<TITLE>Air Force Lt. Turned Firefighter Hero</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Excerpted from EmergencyNet News (ENNFAX)
<BR>
Tuesday-Feb. 27, 1996
<BR>
Vol. 2 - 058
<P>
<B>Hungary...</B>
<P>

<H2>Air Force Lieutenant Turned Firefighter Called Hero</H2>

United States Air Force First Lt. David M. Curry, age 26 from
Duluth, Georgia, turned into a firefighter on Friday night.
Curry helped rescue two people from a burning house and then
returned into the fire building and helped contained the fire.
<P>

Lt. Curry said that he was driving through the Hungarian town
of Kaposavar on official business when he saw a large number of
people watching a house on fire.  Curry said, "I was doing an
errand in town when I saw a thick plume of smoke coming from a
house.  There were 100 to 150 people watching, so I figured it
must be taken care of."
<P>

Curry than just drove past the scene, but he then decided to go
back and take a second look ... something didn't look right to
him.  When he returned to the burning building, he noticed that
the front door was closed.  Curry said, "People don't normally 
close the door behind them when they leave a burning building, so
I asked if anyone had been brought out and, of course, no one had.
Everyone was just watching the house burn down!"
<P>

Lt. Curry made his way through the crowd and kicked the door in.
He helped a small boy and his mother to safety outside of the
burning building and then returned and helped the father battle
the fire upstairs until firefighters arrived.
<P>

Curry said, "As I fought my way through the crowd, everyone looked
at me as if I was from another planet.  But afterwards, the woman's
mother came up to me, put her hand on her heart and just said,
"Ah, Americans!"
<P>

After doing all he could at the scene, Curry returned to his office
and collapsed.  He had suffered smoke inhalation and was hospitalized
overnight on Friday.  Lt. Curry is part of 3,000 troops who are
stationed in Hungary to support the Bosnian peace mission.
<P>
(c) EmergencyNet News Service, 1996, All Rights Reserved.
<P>
