<TITLE>Movie Crew Saves Child in Yonkers, NY</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
Excerpted from ENNFAX Report Vol 2, #47: 02/16/96
<BR>
EmergencyNet News Service
<P>
<H2>MOVIE CREW RESCUES CHILD AT YONKERS FATAL FIRE</H2>
By Jim Fay  ENN NYC-NJ Metro Correspondent
<P>

A movie crew member, filming the upcoming film "The Preacher's
Wife," has been credited with saving the life of a child at
a fire in Yonkers, NY, that also caused the death of two other
young children.
<P>
At approximately 2230 hrs., EST, last night, the Yonkers Fire Department
responded to 5 Van Courtlandt Park Ave., in the Getty Square
section of Yonkers, on initial reports of a frame dwelling fire
with children trapped.  Soon after their arrival, a 2nd alarm was
transmitted, when firefighters saw a heavy fire condition in an
occupied building.
<P>

Just down the block from the fire, the film crew was set up.
Before the arrival of the FD, the crew became aware of the raging
fire, and several of the crew members ran to the scene. An
unidentified member of the crew entered the building and was able
to save one of the children in the fire. Two other children were
found by Yonkers firefighters, but sucumbed to the injuries and
smoke inhalation from the fire.
<P>

The fire soon went to a 3rd Alarm, and two tower ladder streams were
used to extinguish the fire in the three-story frame house, and to
protect the similar type exposures.
<P>

"The Preacher's Wife, staring Whitney Houston and Denzel Washington,
had been in the area most of the day, and had just begun wrapping up
their operation when the fire broke out.  In addition to the
childrens deaths, 14 Yonkers firefighters were also reported injured.
<P>
(c) EmergencyNet News Service, 1996, All Rights Reserved.
<P>
