<BODY>
EmergencyNet News Briefs- 03/14/96
<P>
<IMG SRC="/newsbrf.gif">  <B>California...</B>
<P>
By Evan Platt
<BR>
IncidentNet
<P>
<H2>Fire and Major Accident in California</H2>
<B>Incidents on March 14:</B>
<P>

PALO ALTO, CALIFORNIA - Stanford Mall 3rd alarm, El Camino Real. Fire
in the Empoium Mall.  Mall was scheduled to  be torn down. Cause under
investigation. Fire started at 10:00, quickly went to 3rd due to massive 
size. (40x30 fully involved, multi-story.)  Fire under control at 11:30. 
Red Cross called. Cause under investigation.
<P>
<HR>
			
MOUNTAIN VIEW, CALIFORNIA - major injury accident at approx. 14:00 PST
when a call into the Mountain View  911 center reported a armored car 
had hit a vehicle at the intersection of Latham & Rengstorff. As  a 
precautionary, an engine, truck, and medic was requested. Before any 
units were on scene, dispatch reported "We are recieving ten calls on 
this. It sounds like extrication."
<P>

A second Engine was requested. Upon arrival of the first engine, they 
reported a 1979 Oldsmobile had broadsided a  Armored Transport of 
California armored car. One of the two people from the armored car had 
been ejected, and the people in the Oldsmobile were trapped. A second 
truck, two more medics, and LifeFlight helicopter was activated with a 
landing zone of El Camino & Rengstorff, a VERY busy intersection.  There 
were four people in the Oldsmobile, and the top had to be cut off.
<P>

Four victims were transported via ambulance to Stanford / Valley Med,
and two victims were transported via LifeFlight to San Jose Hospital, 
with one person in critical condition. The Mountain View Police guarded 
the van until a transport unit arrived, since the ATC vehicle was fully 
loaded, and ensured that a transport was made. No money  was lost. A 
second JOL was brought in from Los Altos.
<P>
