<H3>The World's Finest Protection for America's Greatest People</H3>
<P>
3D Medical, Inc. is proud to announce the availability of a new level of personal protection for medical and emergency response workers.  The innovative new product is a high-risk, powder-free, non-allergenic, non-slip latex examination glove. It is the ultimate in protection against both blood borne pathogens and latex protein allergies.
<P>
The new 3D Medical gloves are 10mils in thickness, to afford the wearer an additional measure of protection, while maintaining the maximum sensitivity possible. They are certified to a 1% pinhole level (AQL) to assure the denial of entry of pathogens, and they exceed FDA and ASTM requirements for medical grade exam gloves. The gloves are manufactured to ISO-9000 standards, which are stronger than FDA or ASTM standards for medical grade gloves.
<P>  
In a recent clinical study, conducted by Dr. E. Marcia Boyer of the University of Iowa, 3D Medical's gloves showed a marked decrease in wearer allergic sensitivity. 85% of the previously allergic people, participating in the study, noted a decrease in both the number and intensity of dermatological signs and symptoms when wearing 3D Medical gloves. 3D medical gloves are triple-leached and chlorinated to assure the removal of hand irritating proteins and micro-organisms.
<P>
According to 3D's Ralph Dahm, the high-risk gloves are extremely durable and feature a non-slip finish that will allow emergency and medical professionals to grasp and hold syringes, vacu-tainers, dressings and other equipment, even when they are wet or bloody. Dahm also said that the gloves have a beaded cuff for strength and that they are designed to reduce hand fatigue when worn for extended periods of time. And, 3D Medical gloves are 100% guaranteed to be free of defects.
<P>
The gloves are available in Small, Medium, Large, and Extra-large.
