<HEAD>
<TITLE>Palisades Park, NJ Pursuit/Accident</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
New Jersey...
<BR>
For Immediate Release: 12/04/95-14:00CST
<BR>
<H3>Palisades Park NJ Pursuit/Accident</H3>
<BR>
By James J. Fay, ENN NY/NJ Metro Correspondent
<P>

Palisades Park, NJ, Bergen County (in the vicinity of the George Washington
Bridge)  At approximately  1015 Hrs. EST, Palisades Park Police in pursuit of a
violator resulted in a motor vehicle accident at the intersection of Broad Ave.
and Central Blvd.. The accident involving a "church bus" from a local Korean Church fully occupied with parishoners.  Numerous injuries were reported at the scene and at least one death.
<P> 
Initial reports state that the chase was started with Englewood, NJ,
Police, who reported that the pursued vehicle, a commercial food van, was
stolen in their jurisdiction. It is unknown if the Englewood Police chased 
the wanted vehicle into Palisades Park, or if Palisades Park attempted to 
stop the vehicle based on a raidioed discription. The stolen van crashed 
head-on into the church van and then into another civilian vehicle. Both vans 
then careened into a wall of a building near the Palisades Police Headquaters. 
<P>
The Bergen County Prosecutors Office, assisted by the County Sheriff's Crime 
Scene Unit are investigating the entire incident.
<P>
