<HEAD>
<TITLE>Chicago Murder Weekend</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
For Immediate Release: 12/03/95-12:00CST
<BR>
CPD Police Activity...
<BR>
<H3>Violent Weekend in Chicago</H3>
<BR>
By Steve Macko, ENN Editor
<P>
It is shaping up to be a violent weekend in Chicago.  Several homicides
and shootings have been keeping Violent Crime investigators quite busy.
Special attention is being given to the City's West Side, especially
in the Harrison and Marquette areas, where a gang war seems to be brewing.
<P>  

On Thursday, there were two homicides.  A 44-year-old male was found
shot to death outside of 1236 South Karlov Avenue in the 10th Police
District on the City's West Side.  Police believe that the victim was
dealing in the drugs.  Later, a 37-year-old male was found beaten to
death outside of 2210 West Warren Blvd in the 13th Police District also
on the West Side.  The homicide appears to be the result of a robbery.
<P>

On Friday morning, at about 0245 CST, the still-smoldering body of
a 25-year-old male was found in the alley behind 1331 South Kedvale
Avenue in the 10th Police District on Chicago's West Side.  The victim
was reported to be bound with wire, beaten about the head and set on
fire.
<P>

Another man, this one said to be 43-years-old, was found burning less
than two hours later after the above homicide at 2857 West Taylor Street
in the 11th Police District on Chicago's West Side.  The victim was
transported to Cook County Hospital in critical condition with burns
over 80 percent of his body.  This victim died less than 24 hours later.
Police said that they had no suspects in custody.
<P>

At about 1200 CST on Friday, there was a shooting across the street
from a bus station at 565 West Harrsion Street in the 1st Police District
near Chicago's Loop.  Witnesses said that a man shot two unarmed
security guards.  The two security guards were in a hot dog stand when
one of the victims became involved in an altercation with two patrons.
One of the patrons pulled out a gun and shot both guards.  One of the
guards was killed and the other suffered a serious gunshot wound to the
arm.
<P>

In other homicides from the past few days -- A man was found shot
several times at 815 North Ridgeway Avenue in the 11th Police District.
Police say that this shooting was gang-related.  In the 10th Police 
District, a 20-year-old male was shot to death at 1836 South Karlov
Avenue.  This homicide also appears to be gang-related.
<P>

On Saturday morning, a long-time worker for the City of Chicago Streets
and Sanitation Department was shot and killed during an apparent
carjacking.  The 58-year-old victim's body was found in an alley in
the 1800 block of West Cornelia Avenue in the 19th Police District
on the North Side.  Belmont area investigators were questioning two
suspects on Saturday.
<P>

And finally, the 128th Chicago area bank robbery of the year took place
on Saturday morning at about 0940 CST at the Household Bank located at
5960 West Irving Park Road in the 16th Police District on the City's 
Northwest Side.  A man told a bank teller that he had a gun and fled
with about $2,000 in cash.
<P>
(c) Emergency Response & Research Institute, 1995, All rights reserved.
