<HEAD>
<TITLE>Hostage/Barricade in Colorado</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>*FLASH Traffic*
<BR>
EmergencyNet News Service
<BR>
05/02/96-19:00 CDT
<P>
<H2>Gunman with Possible Explosives Strapped to His Body; Barricaded in Colorado Springs Office Building</H2>
By Clark Staten
<P>

(ENN) A man, believed to be a disgruntled former construction worker, is reportedly holed-up in the main administration building of a family focus forum in Colorado Springs, CO at this hour. According to witnesses, the unidentified gunman has both weapons and explosives and
has held police at bay since 2:30p.m. MDT this afternoon.
<P>

A Colorado Springs police spokesperson, Lt. Allan Scott, said that the man is holding what appears to be a "stick with an electrical switch on it." The 
stick is reportedly connected by wires to a some sort of a satchel strapped to the man's body. He is also reportedly armed with at least one handgun, which 
he kept brandishing and "playing with the hammer."
<P>

At least four hostages were originally taken by the gunman, two men and
two women. After two hours of negotiations with police, all four were 
released. One of the released hostages confirmed that the man had "some sort 
of device" attached to his torso and had talked about "blowing himself up."
<P>

The gunman reportedly entered the conservative Christian "Focus on Family" building in an attempt to redress grievances in regard to a workman's
compensation dispute, in which he didn't feel that he was adequately
compensated for injures he had received while helping to build the
three-story complex.
<P>

According to a police spokesperson, negotiations continue at this time
and police are hopeful of a peaceful resolution. The assailant has not
been identified.
<P>

Emergencynet News Service
<BR>
Emergency Response & Research Institute
<BR>
6348 N. Milwaukee Ave., #312
<BR>
Chicago, IL. 60646
<BR>
(312) 631-3774 - Voice
<BR>
