<TITLE>Major Long Island Fire: 11/16/95 </TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
EmergencyNet NEWS Service
<BR>
Thursday, November 16, 1995 - 1850 EST
<BR>
<P>

***ENN NEWS FLASH***
<P>

Firefighters on Long Island, New York, are presently battling a major
structure fire in the town of HAUPPAUGE at #50 Cabot Court.  Presently,
45 fire departments are on the scene of a well involved commercial 
building with dimensions of 500x500 that is occupied by the American
Tissue Company.  Firefighters have been battling this blaze since
about 1430 EST.  An exterior attack is being conducted with many
ladder pipes and handlines.
<P>

Hauppauge is located in Suffolk County about 30 miles east of
New York City.
<P>
