<HEAD>
<TITLE>Desert Shield-Terrorist Reports</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: 02-14-91-1400 HRS. CST
<BR>
<H3>RENEWED TERRORIST OFFENSIVE</H3>
Chicago, IL. An alleged call from Palestinian "terror-mastermind" Abu
Abbas appears to have been made in response to the reported
U.S. precision bombing of an Iraqi command and control bunker
in Baghdad.  During the past twenty-four (24) hours, some of
the more traditional (i.e. long-standing) insurgent groups
have targeted U.S. facilities in Bonn, Germany and Santiago,
Chile.  Reportedly, this signals a change in insurgent
activity to a higher level.
<P>

Mounting evidence indicates that the configuration of the
"civilian air-raid shelter" in Baghdad, was a communication
and control bunker that had been specially "hardened" for
that purpose.  Military and intelligence sources have
reported that pictures of the interior of the building
demonstrate the use of air-conditioning, data and
communication cables, and other capabilities that would only
be used in a communications facility.
<P>  

A spokeman from the U.S.  Army Corp of Engineers, who 
asked to remain anonymous, said that the mere configuration of 
the construction of the bunker showed that it had significant similarities 
to those commonly constructed for military headquarters.  He pointed
out that the roof was camouflaged, constructed of several
feet of heavily reinforced concrete, and was surrounded by
barbed-war and security fences.  HUMINTEL (Human
intelligence) sources have reported that the building had
been guarded by armed troops and certain portions of the
building were compartmentalized to provide protection against
chemical weapons.
<P>

A Chicago based anti-terrorist analyst reported that he
believes that Saddam Hussein is using the Baghdad bunker
incident as "black propaganda" in a campaign to incite
fundementalist Moslem groups to riot in Coalition partners
and to prompt insurgent operatives to action.  "An
independent analysis of the number of casualties would
indicate that there were far fewer civilians involved in the
incident than are reported, and that Hussein may have
purposely `arranged' the `martyrdom' of these innocent
people", said Clark Staten of the Emergency Response and
Research Institute of Chicago (ERRI).
<P>

"Hussein has been using `Human Shields' since the beginning
of this conflict....it is not unreasonable that he allowed
them to be used as targets in an elaborate propaganda
campaign", Staten continued. "More interesting is the fact
that no source has reported any military casualties in the
incident....a reasonable and prudent observer would suggest
that this is most unusual", the analyst said.  "To suggest
otherwise is to disregard the history and threats of Saddam
Hussein", Staten concluded.
<P>
Reportedly, "spontaneous demonstrations" occured in Iraq,
Turkey, Egypt, Jordan, and Lebanon as a consequence to the
alleged targeting of the "civilian bunker".  According to
CNN's Peter Arnett, numerous Iraqis were marching through the
streets and firing weapons.  He also reported that the crowd
was calling for revenge for the bombing of the bunker in
Baghdad.  The Associated Press and Rueters both reported that
the Baghdad bunker incident has caused increasing unrest
among fundementalist Moslems in other Middle-Eastern cities.
<P>

In a related story, the U. S. Embassy in Bonn, German
received automatic weapons fire from a position that was
located fifty (50) meters from the Embassy buildings.
According to German police sources, a note was left behind
in which the "Red Army Faction" claimed responsibility fro
the attack.  Embassy officials report that there were no
injuries, but that at least fifteen (15) rounds did strike
the building. A note left nearby, with the emblem of the
groups, stated that this attack was in retribution for the
conflict in the Persian Gulf.
<P>

On Thursday, least three separate explosions occured in
Athens and Thessaloniki, Greece.  Police sources reported
that two separate incidents, which occured twenty (20)
minutes apart, were beleived related to an unnamed terrorist
organization that had "infiltrated" Greece and has
perpetrated at least fourteen (14) individual incidents since
the start of the Persian Gulf war.
<P>

Also early on Thursday morning, Israeli time, Igal Carnon of
the Prime Minister Shamir's office issued a warning that, "we
can expect a big increase in terrorist activities in the next
few weeks". He also called for increased surveillance of
embassies and government related buildings. Mr. Carnon
reported that the movement of "revolutionary operatives" was
noted and that guerilla radio communications had increased in
the vicinity of the Israeli/Lebanese border.
<P>

FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: 02-14-91  1400 HRS. CST
<BR>
(c) Emergency Response & Research Institute, 1991
<BR>
All rights reserved.
<P>
