<TITLE>Washington State Report; Great NW</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<B>Washington State...</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/newsbrf.gif"> 
<P>
<H2>News Briefs from the Puget Sound Region:</H2>
By Bob Nelson
<BR>
National Disaster Communication Response Team
<P>

Saturday, April 6, 1996
<BR>     
Police today arrested a suspect in a 
series of shootings along the I-5 corridor, near the Vancouver, BC 
border.  The suspect stands accused of five seperate attacks, one 
of which left a long-haul truck driver paralized from the waist down.  
Police feel confident that the arrest is a solid case and will bring 
this reign of terror to a close.
<P>

Friday, April 5, 1996 
<BR>    Fire ripped through the Eden Roc 
apartments, located in Bellevue, WA today, leaving 18 units 
with up to 40 individuals displaced until at least Monday.  
The fire has suspicious origins and a resident of the origin 
unit was placed in custody by Bellevue Police Department 
investigators.  The American Red Cross has opened a shelter
facility to house displaced residents and will provide long-term 
assistance to those who require same.  The suspect has recently 
been arrested for kicking in the door of a unit below his, claiming 
that he heard machinery operating in the apartment which was, 
"Driving him crazy," according to BPD investigators.
<P>

Thursday, April 4, 1996
<BR>     Tukwila Police Department investigators 
are searching for the owner of a local espresso stand who police 
claim was robbed and abducted.  After the apparent victim's mother 
arrived at the stand for her morning beverage, she noticed suspicious 
activity and entered the enclosed stand where she discovered a towel 
with blood and a missing cash-box.  Three hours later, police discovered 
the victims car behind a department store, engulfed in fire.  Family 
and friends are mounting a substantial search for the victim and have 
offered a cash reward for information leading to his whereabouts.
<P>
(c) EmergencyNet News, 1996
