<title>U.S. Cruise Missiles Strike Iraq</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<p>ENN News Flash Traffic<br>
09/03/96 - 03:15CDT<br>
<br>
<font color="#FF0000"><font size=5><strong>US Initiates Cruise Missile Attack on Iraq</strong></font></font><br>
<br>
(ENN) According to military sources, an attack on command and control nets, Hawk Missile Batteries, and other selected 
targets has been undertaken by American forces this morning. The attack is believed to have begun at approx. 01:30EDT 
and was comprised of approx. 27 cruise missiles. The precision guided munitions were believed launched from both ships 
and at least one specially fitted B-52 bomber. <br>
<br>
Some military experts are speculating that the initial attack with cruise missiles may not be the only strike package that was 
to be launched on Iraq. It is possible that follow-on strikes will be executed by additional waves of planes, and that the 
cruise strike was used to supress radar and air defense systems. U.S. officials, however, have made no statements 
regarding the extent of this initial strike or any possible future strikes that might be carried out.<br>
<br>
Air raid sirens were reportedly heard in Baghdad, according to CNN reporters who are stationed there. The effect of the 
initial barrage of cruise missiles has not be reported by the military or media outlets in the region. ENN will continue to 
monitor this developing story and provide additional details as they become available.<br>
<br>
Auth: C. Staten - 09/03/96 - 03:15CDT<br>
