<HEAD>
<TITLE>Australian Train Crash/Fire Kills Two</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<B>Australia...</B>
<BR>
<H3>Freight Train Crash/Fire Kills Two; Starts Wildfire</H3>

Two freight trains collided and exploded into a huge ball of
flame in western Australia on Sunday morning.  An engineer and
a boy were killed and another engineer was reported to be in
critical condition.
<P>
A fire reported to be half-a-mile long was set off by the collision.
One of the trains was said to be carrying diesel fuel.  Brushfires
were started by the blaze and more than 100 firefighters fought to
contain the flames.  The incident happened on Sunday (01/14/96)
at about 12:30 a.m., about 155 miles east of Perth on the western 
coast of Australia.
<P>
A man, who was first to reach the scene of the crash, said, "There
was a big ball of fire.  I dragged the man out.  He was engulfed in
flames, but I couldn't reach the others, it was too hot.  I could
hear them screaming for help, but there was nothing I could do."
<P>
A police inspector said that one train was traveling west on the
main Perth line and it crashed into the last nine cars of another
train pulling off the main line.  It was believed that the boy, who
was killed, was a family friend of one of the engineers.
<P>
<A HREF="/firepage.htm"><B>Return to the ENN News Page</B></A>
</BODY>
</HTML>

