<TITLE>Warwickshire, UK Fire and Rescue</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<B>United Kingdom...</B>
We always enjoy hearing from firefighters, paramedics and police officers
when they wish to relate some of their exploits.  Your editor received
the following letter today from Firefighter John Chadwick from the
United Kingdom:
<P>
Dear Steve Macko,
<BR>
                 
This incident happened on the 27th December 95.
This was my first rescue since joining the Fire Brigade in over two
years.   My buddy that entered the building with me confirmed this
was his first in ten years.
<P>

<H3>Fire-Fighters rescue a man from his blazing flat in Bedworth
Warwickshire U.K.</H3>

Three Fire Teams, one from Nuneaton and two from Bedworth were
called to the blaze at 6.34 a.m.
<P>

Crews had been told there were reports that people were trapped
inside the Flat in Dark Lane, Bedworth. firefighters using breathing
apparatus entered the flat and after 15 minutes brought one man out
of the building before going back inside to make sure the rest was
clear.
<P>

The man, believed to be in his mid 20s, was taken to the hospital
and was treated for smoke inhalation.  Divisional Fire officer
Ian Cowley, said: "We had to smash the front door to get in the building.
No one else was in the building."
<P>

The fire is thought to have started in an electric meter box under
the staircase. It was the second blaze at the two storey building in
recent weeks. Malcolm Tandy, spokesman for Warwickshire Fire
Service, said: "We have some concern because we have had two fires in
the same property. We may need to launch an investigation."
A Police spokesman confirmed, "Police & Fire brigade are treating the
fire as suspicious."
<P>
Divisional officer Cowley said that smoke detectors had been fitted
inside the building but he did not think they had been triggered by
the fire.  He urged householders to check smoke alarms regularly.
<P>
<B>F.F.  John Chadwick</B>
<P>
(c) EmergencyNet News Service, 1995, All rights reserved.
