<html>

<head>
<title>SR/DR'97 - Organizations On-Line</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#00FFFF">
<p><font color="#FF0000"><font size=6>SR/DR '97</font><font size=4> </font></font><font color="#0000FF">Proudly Presents: <br>
<font size=5>The International Policewomen's Association </font><br>
<br>
The IPA (International Policewomen's Association) was first organized in 1915 and became a &quot;Depression 
Casuality&quot; during the 30's. In 1956, following a CA Women Peace Officer's meeting in San Diego, IPA was 
reorganized under the tutelage of Dr. Lois Higgins, a Chicago Police officer. The name was also changed to 
reflect a new beginning.<br>
<br>
The IAWP was organized primarily to benefit the women in law enforcement. <br>
<br>
In the 70's, as the membership grew, IAWP started meeting for 5 day training seminars. This year's training will 
be held in Birmingham, England - the first time outside of North America.<br>
<br>
The Association spans the globe with male and female members from almost every country. The membership is 
classified as either Active or Associate Memebers, and with their dues, receive the quarterly magazine 
WomenPolice.<br>
<br>
The IAWP Training Conference for 1997 will be held in Dallas, Texas - November 8 -13. We cordially invite 
all law enforcement to come to &quot;The Big D&quot; for an exciting five days.<br>
<br>
<br>
Watch this page for a continual listing of organizations that will be a part of SR/DR '97 - yours may be next ! 
