<TITLE>Spring, 1996 U.S. Public Health Conference</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H3>Spring U.S. Public Heath Service Disaster Conference</H3>

The US Public Health Service will host "Delivering Health and Medical  Services In Catastrophic Disasters 1996."  The conference will be held at  the Town and Country Hotel, San Diego, CA from Sunday, March 17th through  Thursday,March 21st.  Training Courses will run from Saturday, March 16th through Friday, March 22nd.  A complete listing of the conference educational program and training course descriptions is available on the  FEMA Web site.  The URL is http://www.fema.gov/fema/agenda.html
<P>
The theme for the 1996 event includes "Challenges in the Face of Changes in Health Care, Emergency Management, and Man-Caused Risk," followed by four tracks designed around information targeted at health care facility safety officers, public health officials, clinicians, and emergency managers.
<P> 
The program was designed and is supported by the U.S. Public Health Service (host), Department of Defense, Department of Veterans Affairs, Federal Emergency Management Agency, California Department of Health, California Emergency Medical Services Authority, California Governor's Office of Emergency Services, California Specialized Training Institute, Western States Seismic Policy Council, Central United States Earthquake Consortium, San Bernardino County Medical Center, the George Washington University, and the American College of Emergency Physicians.
<P>  
For more information, see the conference agenda at  http://www.fema.gov/fema/agenda.html or call 1-800-USA-NDMS, extension 444.
<P>
