<HEAD>
<TITLE>ERRI Wins (SM) Name Dispute</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
EmergencyNet News Release-03/23/96
<P>
<IMG SRC="/ENEWSLGO.GIF">
<P>
<H2>Web Business Systems, Inc. Acknowledges ERRI Rights to "EmergencyNet" Name</H2>
By: Steve Macko, ENN Managing Editor
<P>
Web Business Systems, Inc., through their attorney Mr. Barry Shapiro, today officially agreed to discontinue their use of the name "EmergencyNet",  as it related to doing business on the World-Wide-Web.  In a letter to ERRI's attorney, Mr. Frank Nagorka of the Chicago-based Mora & Baugh law firm, Mr. Shapiro acknowledged ERRI's intellectual property rights in regard to the name and advised that the <I><B>emergencynet.com</B> </I>website has been shut-down.
<P>
According to Nagorka, the announcement was the result of a series of letters, faxes, and phone calls that outlined ERRI's position in regard to it's registered ownership of the name and intellectual concept of an "EmergencyNet", that provides news and information to Fire/Police/EMS/Disaster/Counter-Terrorist/Military and other related emergency personnel. Nagorka said, "This letter reaffirms ERRI's rights to the name 'EmergencyNet', particularly as it relates to the provision of emergency news on the Web."
<P>

Clark Staten, ERRI's executive director, said, "I'm glad that we could settle this without going to court; it could have been a costly and protracted situation for both parties..but, one in which I am sure we would have eventually prevailed."  "But, this agreement is a far more civilized and professional solution...we wish Web Business Systems nothing but the best as they choose a new name and proceed with their web marketing plans," Staten concluded.
<P>

Today's decision was the result on a legal challenge that was begun before Web Business Systems, Inc. actually went on-line with a Website named "Emergency Net", that was seen to be in conflict with the already established "EmergencyNet News Service", which is featured at http://www.emergency.com/ennday.htm.  To see the original story, <A HREF="/leglannc.htm"><B>Click Here to see the original Feb. 15 legal announcement</B></A>
<P>
Specific questions, comments or suggestions regarding the agreement, intellectual property matters, or other emergency service legal matters can be directed to Mr. Frank Nagorka, EMT-P, JD at <A HREF="mailto:frankemtp@aol.com"><B>Click here to send mail to Mr. Nagorka</B></A>
<P>
<HR>
<A HREF="/ennday.htm"><B>Return to the ENN News Page</B></A>
<P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
