<head>
<title>Violence Continues in Israel - Day 3</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<p>SNS Special Bulletin<br>
EmergencyNet News -Special Report<br>
09/27/96 - 13:45CDT<br>
<br>
<font size=5><strong>Violence Continues At Numerous Locations in Israel</strong></font><br>
<br>
1:27pm.(Jerusalem time)<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>East Jerusalem </strong></font></p>
<p>According to East Jerusalem Hospitals, there are at least three Arabs that were killed by police gunfire on the Temple 
Mount following the Friday Moslem prayer service. Rioting broke out there and there are undoubtedly civilian casualties.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Tul Karem </strong></font></p>
<p>It appears that several Border Policemen were injured by terrorist gunfire in the attack that took place at the IDF 
checkpoint near PLO-controlled Tul Karem. One is in critical condition. Some of the injured were transported to Laniado 
Hospital in Netanya. IDF helicopters are flying over the area.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Bet Lechem</strong></font></p>
<p>PLO Police are keeping rioters away from Rachel's Tomb. IDF units are on hand and Israeli sharpshooters are in position 
in case the violence escalates.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Kalkilya </strong></font></p>
<p>Violence is erupting as hundreds of Arabs have begun violent demonstrations. IDF troops and Border Policemen are 
moving in with tear gas to control the mob.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Jenin </strong></font></p>
<p>Arabs are out of control in PLO-controlled Jenin. Reports from there are sketchy, but injuries have been reported.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Nachal Oz </strong></font></p>
<p>In Gaza, near Kibbutz Nachal Oz, IDF troops and Arab rioters are battling it out. Shots are being fired. No detailed 
information regarding injuries is available at this time.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Jericho </strong></font></p>
<p>PLO troops are firing at IDF soldiers. Several Israelis were reported injured. Rock and bottle throwing continues.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Kfar Darom </strong></font></p>
<p>In the area of the community of Kfar Darom, Gaza, thousands of rioting Arabs are gathering in front of the gate and are 
beginning to engage the Israeli security troops. The women and children of Kfar Darom are heading for cover as the first 
response security teams are taking positions. This follows heavy fighting and shooting in Kfar Darom yesterday. <br></p>
<hr>
<p><em><strong>Update as of 14:30 (Jerusalem time)</strong></em></p>
<p><img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11><font size=4><strong> The Triangle </strong></font></p>
<p>The area inside Israel, known as the Triangle, has also erupted. The predominantly Arab population has begun throwing 
rocks at Jewish vehicles. Residents of Jaljulia are throwing rocks at Israeli police.<br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Tabia</strong></font></p>
<p>Arab children from the town of Taiba are said to be attacking Jewish cars traveling on the main road. <br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Bus Attacked </strong></font></p>
<p>An Egged bus traveling to the community of Shilo (Shomron - Benjamin Regional Council) was attacked by stone throwers 
near the entrance to Shilo. The attackers were from the nearby village of Turmus Ai'ya. The bus sustained damage but no 
injuries were reported. <br>
<br>
<img src="Redtrngl.gif" align=bottom width=11 height=11> <font size=4><strong>Overall Situation Report and Analysis</strong></font></p>
<p>Violent rioting continues to be reported as of 14:30 (local) near Rachel's Tomb in Bet Lechem (Bethlehem), Kfar Darom 
(Gaza), and Nachal Oz (Gaza). Tens of Arabs have been reported injured in a variety of locations today. </p>
<p>Yasir Arafat, PLO President, has reportedly issued orders to PLO Authority police to discontinue firing at IDF troopers 
and Israeli police. Mixed results have been reported in regard to the success of these efforts. Gunbattles continue in some 
areas involving firefights between the opposing forces. </p>
<p>(Sources: The Israeli SNS News, IDF Sources, Israeli TV and Radio, Shortwave reports, and several Israeli citizens all 
contributed to this continuing series of reports.)</p>
