<P>
To: All Our Friends and Business Associates <P>
FROM:   The Emergency Response &amp; Research Institute<BR>
The EmergencyNet NEWS Service<BR>
The Emergency BBS On-line Services<P>
At this year comes to a close, we wanted to take a few minutes to remember <BR>
the activities of 1995 and reflect on the support and encouragement that we have<BR>
received from so many people during the formative stages of our new business<BR>
endeavor.  In many cases, we certainly couldn't have accomplished what<BR>
we have, without the unique talents and abilities of our friends and associates.<P>
What makes this situation so noteworthy is the fact that most of the people in our<BR>
lives have significant responsibilities of their own, and yet they constantly take the <BR>
time to help, advise, and guide us through the trials and tribulations of everyday<BR>
life.  Time and time again, even in the midst of chaos and grief, those that are <BR>
important to us have been there when the chips were down.  We sincerely<BR>
wanted you to know how much we truly appreciate your time and efforts on<BR>
our behalf.<P>
1995 has been an extremely busy and challenging year for us, and am I am sure<BR>
for all of you.  And yet,  we are confidant that the coming years will prove to be the                 most rewarding of our lives.  Certainly, the past couple of years have been a period of transition that have tested our commitment to private enterprise and entrepreneurship. We continue to look forward to the challenge.<P>
<img src="xmaslt01.gif"align=right><P>
Thank you for your kindness, consideration, and support in the past year. Please 
accept our warmest wishes for a happy holiday season and a healthy and prosperous New Year. We will look forward to seeing/hearing from all of you 
in 1996. Please feel free to contact us if we may ever be of service.<P>
Clark Staten<BR>
Executive Director<BR>
Christmas, 1995 <BR>

