<title>Infrared Radar Image of Bertha - 07/12/96</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p>&#160;</p>
<p align=center><font color="#FF0000"><font size=5>Hurricane Bertha Infrared Enhanced Satellite Image</font></font></p>
<p align=center><img src="Berth11.gif" align=bottom width=383 height=218></p>
<p align=center><font color="#FF0000"><font size=4>02:15Zulu (GMT) 07/12/96 - Courtesy; National Weather Service</font></font></p>
<p>WWUS31 KCHS 120147<br>
HLSCHS<br>
SCZ042&gt;045-047&gt;050-501-502-GAZ101-116&gt;119-137&gt;141-501-120430-<br>
<br>
<font color="#FF0000"><font size=5>HURRICANE BERTHA...LOCAL STATEMENT</font></font><br>
<font color="#FF0000">NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE CHARLESTON SC</font><br>
<font color="#FF0000">935 PM EDT THU JUL 11 1996</font><br>
<br>
<font color="#FF0000">...A HURRICANE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FOR THE ENTIRE SOUTH CAROLINA<br>
COAST AND COASTAL GEORGIA FROM BRUNSWICK NORTHWARD...<br>
...AN INLAND HIGH WIND WARNING WILL BE IN EFFECT FOR TROPICAL STORM<br>
FORCE WINDS IN BERKELEY AND DORCHESTER COUNTIES...<br>
...A FLASH FLOOD WATCH WILL BE IN EFFECT FOR CHARLESTON...BERKELEY AND<br>
DORCHESTER COUNTIES THROUGH FRIDAY...</font><br>
<br>
IN THE CHARLESTON AREA...GOVERNOR DAVID BEASLEY IS STRONGLY URGING<br>
RESIDENTS OF ALL BARRIER ISLANDS AND BEACHFRONT PROPERTY TO MOVE INLAND<br>
IMMEDIATELY...WITH SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON DEWEES ISLAND...THE ISLE OF<br>
PALMS...SULLIVANS ISLAND AND FOLLY ISLAND. SHOULD BERTHA BEGIN MOVING<br>
ON A MORE NORTHWESTERLY COURSE THAN THE OFFICIAL FORECAST TRACK...THESE<br>
AREAS COULD BE AFFECTED BY FLOOD CONDITIONS AND SEVERE WEATHER WITH<br>
WINDS POSSIBLY NEAR HURRICANE FORCE. THIS VOLUNTARY EVACUATION MAY<br>
PROGRESS TO A MANDATORY EVACUTATION LATER TONIGHT. PLEASE MONITOR<br>
REPORTS AND MOVE INLAND TO ENSURE YOUR SAFETY.<br>
<br>
AT 900 PM THE CENTER OF HURRICANE BERTHA WAS LOCATED APPROXIMATELY 150<br>
MILES SOUTHEAST OF SAVANNAH AND 190 MILES SOUTHEAST OF CHARLESTON.<br>
BERTHA IS MOVING TOWARD THE NORTH-NORTHWEST NEAR 10 MPH AND THIS MOTION<br>
IS EXPECTED TO CONTINUE. THE MAXIMUM SUSTAINED WINDS WERE AROUND 80<br>
MPH...WITH LITTLE SIGNIFICANT CHANGE IN STRENGTH EXPECTED BEFORE<br>
LANDFALL.<br>
<br>
THE LATEST TRACK FORECAST BRINGS BERTHA APPROXIMATELY 120 MILES EAST OF<br>
SAVANNAH AT 2 AM. DURING FRIDAY MORNING...BERTHA IS EXPECTED TO PASS<br>
50 MILES TO THE EAST OF CHARLESTON. BERTHA IS FORECASTED TO MAKE<br>
LANDFALL AROUND THE UPPER SOUTH CAROLINA COAST.<br>
<br>
...WIND INFORMATION...<br>
A MAJOR THREAT FROM HURRICANE BERTHA WILL BE THE HIGH WINDS WHICH WILL<br>
CONTINUE TO INCREASE OVERNIGHT. AS OF 900 PM SUSTAINED WINDS WERE ABOUT<br>
20 MPH INLAND AND 30 MPH NEAR THE COAST. THE HIGHEST REPORTED WIND GUST<br>
WAS 50 MPH FROM DOWNTOWN CHARLESTON. NEAR THE IMMEDIATE SOUTH CAROLINA<br>
COAST SUSTAINED WINDS WILL INCREASE TO 40 TO 50 MPH WITH STRONGER GUSTS<br>
UP TO 65 MPH POSSIBLE.<br>
<br>
...RAINFALL INFORMATION...<br>
HEAVY RAINFALL WILL OCCUR THROUGH EARLY FRIDAY MORNING WITH A POTENTIAL<br>
FOR FLOODING AS RAIN BANDS AND OCCASIONAL SQUALLS MOVE ONSHORE.<br>
RAINFALL AMOUNTS AS OF 900 PM WERE ESTIMATED AT 1 TO 2 INCHES. TOTAL<br>
RAINFALL WILL REACH UP TO 4 TO 5 INCHES OR MORE. LOW-LYING AND POOR<br>
DRAINAGE AREAS WILL BE MOST AT RISK FOR FLOOD PROBLEMS.<br>
<br>
...COASTAL FLOODING...<br>
STRONG NORTHEAST WINDS WILL CONTINUE TO PRODUCE HEAVY SURF OVERNIGHT<br>
AND EARLY FRIDAY...WITH BEACH EROSION AND DANGEROUS RIP CURRENTS.<br>
DURING THE HIGH TIDE PERIOD FROM 4 AM TO 8 AM FRIDAY...TIDE DEPARTURES<br>
OF 2 TO 4 FEET ABOVE NORMAL ARE POSSIBLE. SIGNIFICANT COASTAL FLOODING<br>
WILL BE POSSIBLE...ESPECIALLY IN COMBINATION WITH ANY HEAVY RAINFALL.<br>
<br>
...TIDE INFORMATION...<br>
THE FOLLOWING ARE TIMES AND NORMAL LEVELS OF TIDES FOR...<br>
<br>
SAVANNAH BEAUFORT CHARLESTON HARBOR<br>
HIGH TIDE FRI 621 AM (7.8) 725 AM (6.8) 624 AM (4.8)<br>
<br>
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION IS CONTAINED IN PUBLIC INFORMATION STATEMENTS<br>
UNDER THE IDENTIFIER CAEPNSCHS AND SHORT TERM FORECASTS...IDENTIFIER<br>
CAENOWCHS...ISSUED BY THIS OFFICE. THE NEXT STATEMENT WILL BE ISSUED AROUND 
MIDNIGHT.<br>
<br>
LAVIS/LJP/MRV<br>
</p>
