<html>

<head>
<title>Nashville; Music City USA</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body background="file:///D:/Graphics/blue_paper.gif">
<p><font color="#FF0000"><font size=6>Nashville </font></font><br>
<br>
<font color="#0000FF"><font size=5>Music City USA</font></font><br>
<br>
<font color="#0000FF"><strong>Big things are stirring in Music City....</strong><br>
<br>
For the city that was country before it was cool, music is the keynote in its roster of activities. Renovations to the 
Ryman Auditorium, known as the &quot;Mother Church of Country Music,&quot; have restored the concert hall to its former 
glory days when it was the city's premier performance facility and later the home of the Grand Ole Opry. We'll keep 
you updated as 1997 show dates are announced.<br>
<br>
The District, a 16 square block in the heart of downtown, keeps bringing people back with more to do during the 
day and into the night. Planet Hollywood lands in The District with movie memorabilia and merchandise as well as 
the Apple Strudel that made Mother Schwarzenegger famous way before her son hit it the big time. Having the blues 
is a good thing as B.B. King's Blues Club and Restaurant brings &quot;the world's premier blues address&quot; to Lower 
Broadway. With dozens of shops, restaurants, and clubs, The District has something for everyone.<br>
<br>
Don't forget Music Row ! Fabulous food and shopping surround the Country Music Hall of Fame, a &quot;must see&quot; for 
all music lovers. Other possibilities include a stop at Barbara Mandrels Museum, or the recording studios of RCA, 
Warner Brothers, United Artists Arista, MCA, or Columbia.<br>
<br>
Speaking of shopping...<br>
In addition to shops in The District and Music Row, Nashville has a &quot;new&quot; mall. Located off I-440, 100 Oaks, 
Nashville's very first mall, was recently made contemporary with a massive renovation that transformed it into a 
750,000 square-foot, value-oriented upscale shopping center with stores like Saks Off Fifth, Luxury Linens, and 
Media Play. Don't miss it!<br>
<br>
Opryland USA ....<br>
A destination in itself. Located approximately 15 minutes from downtown Nashville is the fabulous Opryland Hotel 
and Theme Park. From the spectacular 4.5 acre indoor water gardens to the specialty restaurants and shops, this 
1,800 room hotel is Southern hospitality at its grandest. Spend an afternoon at the Springhouse Golf Club, or cruising 
on the General Jackson, the world's largest showboat. Close out your day with a visit to the Grand Ole Opry, the 
tradition continues today in what has become Opryland USA.</font><br>
<br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.emergency.com/srdr97/index.htm"><strong>Return to Home Page</strong></a></p>
</body>

</html>
