<H2>
<HR>
<IMG BORDER="0" SRC="Sph0012.gif" WIDTH="25" HEIGHT="25"> <A NAME="Internet Skills">Internet Skills</A> </H2>
<H3><FONT COLOR="Red">Using the World Wide Web as an Instructional Tool</FONT></H3>
<UL>
<LI><B>Navigating</B> : Moving around the Web, including finding specific locations and taking advantage of many features of a Web browser.</LI>
<LI><B>Information Gathering</B> : Effectively making use of search engines to find and retrieve information, using keywords, and refining searches.</LI>
<LI><B>Communicating</B> : Making use of various communications capabilities, including sending and receiving e-mail and using chat rooms, listserves, and news groups.</LI>
<LI><B>Publishing</B> : Including, among other things, developing and posting a home page and finding a way to post the home page on a server so that others can access it, as well as maintaining the home page so those ideas, links, etc., are kept up-to-date.</LI>
</UL>
