<B><H1><I>
DAVIS COUNTY SCHOOL DISTRICT 
EMERGENCY PREPAREDNESS 
</H1></B><BR></I>
<BODY><BODY BGCOLOR="#FBF4BD"><HR>
<B><H3>C.E.R.T. - Community Emergency Response Team </H3></B><BR>
<H4>Learn to help your family and neighbors in the event of an emergency.  
	In the schools, train to help the students and fellow faculty members.
	How do I get involved?  Where can I get some training?  What kind of 
	training will I receive?  Is there inservice credit available?  And more... 
</H4><ul><ul><A HREF=" cert.htm">
<H5>  More Information About CERT  </A><BR></H5></ul></ul><HR>

<B><H3>C.A.R.P. - Child Access Routing Plans </H3></B><BR>
<H4> What is the safest route your child can take to and from school? 
           Who decides which route to take?  How can I get involved?  And more...
</H4><ul><ul><A HREF=" carp.htm">
<H5>  More Information About CARP  </A><BR></H5></ul></ul><HR>

<B><H3>Davis County Schools Emergency Preparedness </H3></B><BR>
<H4> What is in the District Plan?  What does a school plan look like?  What about flip charts?
	When is my school holding their emergency preparedness week?  And more.... 
</H4><ul><ul><A HREF="emerprep.htm">
<H5>  More Information About Emergency Preparedness  </A><BR></H5></ul></ul><HR>

 <B><H3>Red Cross Shelter Management </H3></B><BR>
<H4> In the event of an emergency, the District has an agreement with the American
          Red Cross to use our schools as shelters.  How will we accomplish this?  What about
          training? 
</H4><ul><ul><A HREF="shelter.htm">
<H5>  More Information About Red Cross Shelter Management  </A><BR></H5></ul></ul><HR>

