<BODY BACKGROUND="Paper12l.jpg">
<H3 ALIGN="center">TOURBUS</H3>
<P ALIGN="left">    /~~~|~~~~|~~~~|~~~~|~~~~|~~~~|~~~~|~~~~|~~~~|~~~~~/~~~|~\<BR>
&gt;     |____|____|____|____|____|____|____|____|____|____/    |  \<BR>
&gt;     |                                                /_____|---\<BR>
&gt;    /  --T-H-E---I-N-T-E-R-N-E-T---T-O-U-R-B-U-S--&gt;  ///////|    |<BR>
&gt;   |                                                |///////|    |<BR>
&gt;   ~~~/~~~\~/~~~\~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\~~~\~~~~<BR>
&gt;      \___/ \___/  &quot;Why Surf When U Can Ride The Bus?&quot;  \___/</P>
<P>TOURBUS - &copy; 1995, Patrick Crispen and Bob Rankin<BR>
All rights reserved.</P>
<P>TOURBUS is a project by the above mentioned authors who send, through e-mail, information on Internet sites that are of interest to educators. These &quot;Bus Stops&quot; cover a wide variety of topics. Some are instructional (like how to use audio over the Internet) and others give lists of great sites for students to visit.</P>
<P>I have been on their &quot;tour&quot; for over a year now and have found it interesting enough to place here on our district home page. Below is information on how to <U>subscribe</U>, <U>unsubscribe</U> and how to find their <U>archives</U>. (There are past issues that date back over a year.) If you have any questions, you can contact me (<A HREF="mailto:rmartin@curric.dist.davis.k12.ut.us">Roger Martin</A>) by phone at 451-1181 or through email at rmartin@curric.dist.davis.k12.ut.us</P>
<P><U><B>How to subscribe</B></U></P>
<P>Send e-mail to LISTSERV@LISTSERV.AOL.COM</P>
<P>and in the body of the message, enter this command:</P>
<P>SUBSCRIBE TOURBUS Firstname Lastname</P>
<P><B><U>How to unsubscribe</U></B></P>
<P>Send e-mail to LISTSERV@LISTSERV.AOL.COM</P>
<P>and in the body of the message,enter this command:</P>
<P>UNSUBSCRIBE TOURBUS your-email-address</P>
<P><B><U>To look at past issues in the Archives</U></B></P>
<P>http://www.worldvillage.com/tourbus.htm
<HR>
<A HREF="http://www.davis.k12.ut.us">Return to Davis Home Page</A></P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
