<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Sports/Activities

</H1>
<P>Davis District athletes have won 126 state championships since 1937, with  107 of  
these coming to Davis schools since since 1968.  The public is invited to attend all games.
</P>
<P>The District has outstanding athletic programs, (in seven high schools) which 
include seventeen sports:  
</P>
<UL>
<LI>football      </LI>
<LI>basketball, boys and girls</LI>
<LI>     golf
</LI>
<LI>baseball     </LI>
<LI>swimming, boys and girls     </LI>
<LI>drill team
</LI>
<LI>softball</LI>
<LI>      soccer, boys and girls</LI>
<LI>     volleyball
</LI>
<LI>wrestling</LI>
<LI>     track, boys and girls</LI>
<LI>     cross country, boys and girls
</LI>
<LI>                   tennis, boys and girls
</LI>
</UL>




<P>
All athletics are sponsored by the Utah High School Activities Association.
</P>
<P>The public is invited to attend all games.
</P>
<P><B>Athletic Information Office, 451-1113</B>
</P>
<P>&nbsp;
</P>
<P>A variety of extracurricular, academic activities are offered in the secondary 
and elementary schools.  Some of these are:  
</P>
<UL>
<LI> Academic Olympiad</LI>
<LI>      FBLA (Future Business 
Leaders      National Honor Society
</LI>
<LI> Cheerleading          of America)      </LI>
