</LI>
<LI> Debate</LI>
<LI>      Foreign Language Clubs</LI>
<LI>      Various musical groups
</LI>
<LI> DECA (Distributive Education Clubs of America)</LI>
<LI>    -      Geography  Bee</LI>
<LI>      VICA 
(Vocational IndustrialClubs of America)
</LI>
<LI>     JETS (Junior Engineering     
     Technical Society)
</LI>
<LI>Drama          </LI>
</UL>






<P>Call the school for further information.           
</P>
<H1>                             
Applied Technology Education
</H1>
<H3>(Vocational/Technical Education)
</H3>
<P>Applied Technology Education programs offer a sequence of courses which 
prepare individuals for employment in current or emerging occupations requiring other than 
a baccalaureate or advanced degree.  Programs at the junior high level provide 
foundation courses for the trades and technical fields.
</P>
<P>Students enrolled in ATE programs are involved in competency-based applied 
learning which encourages and instills academic knowledge, higher-order reasoning and 
problem-solving skills, work attitudes, general employability skills, and the 
occupational-specific skills necessary for economic independence as a productive and contributing member 
of society.
</P>
<P>In Davis School District, over 90% of more than 27,048 secondary students 
participate in vocational/technical training which includes six major program areas:  home 
economics, health occupations, business, marketing, agriculture, and trade and industrial.  196 
staff members, offering 106 different courses, prepare students with a foundation for 
immediate employment or additional training, and a future of lifelong learning.
</P>
<P><B>Vocational Education, 451-1154</B></P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
