<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Advanced Placement Program

</H1>
<P>All Davis high schools offer advanced placement classes to college-bound students. 
 Classes include American history, European history, government, biology, 
chemistry, physics, computer science, English composition and literature, French, German, 
Latin, Spanish, mathematics, music and art.
</P>
<P>In 1995, Davis students took a total of 2,958 A.P. exams of which 2,113 exams or 
71% were passed successfully, each worth 12 hours of college credit.  
</P>
<P>Every student who passes a 12-credit A.P. exam saves college expenses for tuition, 
room and board, textbooks, etc.
</P>
<P>Davis and Utah high schools are noted for the strong participation in 
advanced placement classes which are college-level courses.
</P>
<P><B>A. P. Program,  451-1105 </B></P>
<H1>
Bilingual Education
</H1>
<P>The Bilingual Education Program provides instructional services through 
one-on-one assistance and English as a Second Language (ESL) Centers to students from 
different cultures.  They are presently serving students from 58  different schools in the District.  
Over 3,000 students have been identified, representing 52 different languages.
</P>
<P><B>Bilingual Education, 451-1161</B></P>
<H1>
Chapter I Program
</H1>
<P>Over 3,000 Chapter I students will be served this year by the Davis Chapter I 
project in 18 elementary schools and two junior  high schools.  One-to-one tutoring in 
reading, language and math involve a large tutoring staff.
</P>
<P>
P<B>eer Tutoring, 451-1116</B></P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
