<BODY BGCOLOR="#c6d3ad">
<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Alternative High Schools

</H1>
<H3>Mountain High School
</H3>
<P>Mountain High School serves students in grades 10 through 12 who are seeking 
an alternative educational experience.  The schools seeks to serve these students by 
providing a flexible and personalized school climate where students' pace of progress 
toward graduation is based upon their willingness to engage in the work of the school.  
Mountain High School has an extended day (7:30 a.m. to 7:00 p.m.) and an extended school 
calendar year (August - June).
</P>
<P>Three approaches to study are available to students at Mountain High School.
</P>
<P><B>Team Studies</B> emphasizes curricular integration and community-based 
learning activities.  Teachers and students work together on projects based on 
<I>Core Curriculum </I>standards with the objective of creating tangible products that demonstrate 
students' mastery of the standards.
</P>
<P><B>Directed Studies</B> emphasizes both curricular standards and student accountability. 
 Students earn credit by meeting standards of work completed, mastery as demonstrated 
by testing, and the keeping of time commitments.  Students may schedule hours according 
to personal needs, but are expected to keep the scheduled commitments they make.
</P>
<P><B>Home Studies</B> recognizes that a student may face circumstances that make 
attendance at school impossible.  Students earn credit by completing school work at home, with 
the expectation that 25-30 hours will be spent weekly on school work.  Weekly 
appointments with home study teachers or assistants provide time for tutoring and mastery testing.
</P>
<P>Students at Mountain High School may enroll in studies at the Davis Applied 
Technology Center or in other applied technology courses at Davis High School.  Mountain High 
School is fully accredited and follows Davis School District requirements for graduation.
</P>
<P><B>Mountain High School, 546-7960</B></P>
<P><B></B>
</P>
<H1>
Young Parents School
</H1>
<P>Young Parents School serves high school aged parents and expecting parents 
who choose not to remain in their home school.  The school emphasizes the academic 
core curriculum as well as parenting skills.  On-campus child care is available to students for 
a small monthly fee.  The school emphasizes a climate of support and provides 
opportunities for both personal and academic counseling.
</P>
<P>Students who attend Young Parents may receive diplomas from their home high 
schools and attend commencement exercises if they choose.  Students at Young Parents may 
enroll in studies at the Davis Applied Technology Center or in other applied technology 
courses at Davis High School.  Young Parents School is fully accredited and follows Davis 
School District requirements for graduation.
</P>
<P><B>Young Parents School, 546-7970</B></P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
