<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Building Energy Systems

</H1>
<P>There are many advantages to having a central system for energy.  With a 
computerized energy management system helping to operate the District's buildings' energy 
systems (heating, ventilating, air conditioning and some corridor and outside lighting), the 
District is getting a higher value for energy dollars.
</P>
<P>Based upon BTU's per square foot that were used in the buildings before the 
energy system was installed  and the current BTU's, the overall savings is between two and 
three million dollars a year.
</P>
<P>Because the energy system has report-back capabilities, security and fire 
protection systems were added at a nominal cost.
</P>
<H1>School Security
</H1>
<P>The security number for the District is 774-7670 (answered 24 hours a day).  
Citizens are encouraged to call reporting vandalism, property damage or suspicious activities at 
any school property.
</P>
<P><B>Security, 774-7670</B></P>
<H1><A NAME="HR">Human Resources</A> 
</H1>
<P>The District employs approximately 2,000 part-time and 3,600 full-time employees.  
The Human Resources Department handles a variety of personnel related issues, including:
</P>
<UL>
<LI>     Recruitment and selection of staff
</LI>
<LI>     Equal employment opportunity
</LI>
<LI>     Insurance benefits
</LI>
<LI>     Personnel policy
</LI>
<LI>     Personnel records
</LI>
<LI>     Substitute System
</LI>
</UL>





<P><B>Human Resources, 451-1103</B></P>
