<BODY BGCOLOR="#c6d3ad">
<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Crisis Team

</H1>
<P>The Davis District Crisis Team is composed of social workers, psychologists 
and counselors who have been trained in crisis response, suicide and other traumas.  
They volunteer their time for crisis work.  The team assembles at a school, by invitation of 
the principal, when the death of a student or faculty member has occurred.  In 
coordination with the school's existing mental health professionals, the team conducts crisis groups 
with students who have been impacted.
</P>
<P>In the group, students are encouraged to express grief, to develop a strategy for 
coping with the crisis and to identify peers and adults who can be their support network.  In 
the event of a suicide, crisis workers ask for a commitment from each group member not 
to copy the suicide.
</P>
<P>The team notifies the parents of students identified as being at-risk, and 
encourages them to get immediate mental health intervention.
</P>
<P>The goals of the crisis team are to prevent copycat suicides, offer grieving 
students emotional support and enable students to develop coping strategies. Support 
systems identify students at-risk for self-destructive behavior for an immediate referral.  The 
crisis team acts as an early response team, meeting the initial needs of the school during a 
crisis, but doesn't do long-term counseling with students.
</P>
<H3>
After Hours Student Assistance
</H3>
<P>
The Drug Free Schools Program provides after school group services, as requested 
by individual schools, for at-risk students needing intervention in such areas as 
divorce adjustment, school adjustment, anger management, violence prevention, coping skills, 
and grief.  Follow-up services are available for students impacted by a peer's suicide.  
Referral to more intensive intervention sources is made when indicated.
</P>
<P>
<B>Crisis Team, 451-1159</B></P>


<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
