<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Curriculum and Instruction

</H1>
<P>In conjunction with the Davis District Strategic Plan, the curriculum department 
and instructional staff are moving in the following directions:
</P>
<UL>
<LI>     Continued refinement and use of the K-6 Student Education Plan (SEP) and 7-12 
Student Education Occupation Planning (SEOP) that involves the student, parents, teachers 
and counselors as they plan for educational needs and goals.
</LI>
<LI>     Insuring that the Davis Course of Study is responsive and reflective of students' 
needs in an ever-changing society.
</LI>
<LI>     Continual support for integration of subject content areas  math, science, 
language arts, social studies, art, music, healthy life-styles, and applied technology education.
</LI>
<LI>     Continued support, through a partnership with Davis County School District and 
D.C. Heath and Company,  for the pilot and implementation of integrated learning programs.
</LI>
<LI>     The exploration of religious, cultural and ethnic diversity to broaden and enrich 
the curriculum while perpetuating and improving the values of equality and equity.
</LI>
<LI>     Continued efforts to improve effective teaching and learning in the basic subjects 
of math, science, social studies and language skills.
</LI>
<LI>     Instructional strategies that assist students identified as &quot;at-risk&quot; in learning.
</LI>
<LI>     Continued emphasis on critical and creative thinking and problem solving skills in 
all areas of curriculum.
</LI>
<LI>     Use of standardized test scores to assess student achievement and evaluate 
instructional strategies and content alignment.
</LI>
<LI>     Provide support for and implementation of the &quot;School-to-Career&quot; and 
&quot;Comprehensive Guidance&quot; programs.
</LI>
<LI>     Provide a variety of professional development (in-service) activities for district 
staff members.
</LI>
<LI>     Support staff training and implementation of the newly adopted elementary 
and secondary language, reading and literature educational materials.
</LI>
<LI>     Continue implementation of the high school graduation options (Seals) program 
for students.
</LI>
</UL>












<P><B>Curriculum  Department, 451-1102</B></P>
