<BODY BGCOLOR="#c6d3ad">
<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Child Care - Preschool Programs

</H1>
<H3>Cooperative Preschool
</H3>
<P>The cooperative preschool program allows parents to work with the teacher 
in providing an excellent experience for their child.  The program, located throughout 
the District, is self-supporting and charges a tuition.  
</P>
<H3>Pre kindergarten Developmentally Delayed
</H3>
<P>Children who meet specific criteria to be classified as developmentally delayed 
are provided with a free, appropriate public education.  Transportation is provided to 
locations throughout Davis County.  For assessment to determine eligibility, call Family 
Enrichment Center, 546-7309.
</P>
<H3>High School Child Development Centers
</H3>
<P>Full-time Child Development Centers operate in conjunction with the Child 
Development programs at all seven high school locations.  High school students receive 
training in the healthy growth and development of young children in preparation for 
successful parenting and child care professions.  Full-time care is available to children of 
district employees only.  Limited enrollment is available to the public for the preschool component. 
 Programs differ at each high school.  For more information contact the child 
care coordinator at the local high school or Mary Lou Seamons at 451-1336.
</P>
<P><B>Early Intervention Education, 451-1039</B></P>
<H1>
Head Start
</H1>
<P>Davis County Head Start is a comprehensive child development program for 
low income families.  Head Start offers services in the areas of education, social services, 
health, nutrition and parent involvement.  Head Start also offers services to children 
with disabilities.
</P>
<P>Several options are available through Head Start:
</P>
<P>1.     Classroom:  Four days per week.  Child must be four years old on or before 
September 1.
</P>
<P>2.     Home-based:  One home visit, one classroom experience each week.  Child must 
be three years old on or before September 1.
</P>
<P>3.     Parent and Child Center:   Parents and children meet with Head Start staff 1-2 times 
per week.  This program is for pregnant women, infants and toddlers.
</P>
<P><B>Family  Enrichment Center, 546-7309</B></P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
