</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#c6d3ad">
<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Davis School District Foundation

</H1>
<P>The Davis School District Foundation is a non-profit organization interested 
in improving our public schools.  Led by private citizens of various communities 
and professions, the Foundation secures contributions from private sources to fund 
enrichment and learning projects which cannot be funded through the normal budgetary process.
</P>
<P>It encourages businesses and individuals to forge an essential partnership with 
an individual school, a specific program or the complete district educational system.
</P>
<P>One person, one company or one contribution can make a vital difference.  The 
quality of a community's public school system is a key factor in the quality of life and the 
attraction of new business.
</P>
<P>All contributions are tax deductible to the extent of the law.  Gifts may be used for 
a designated purpose.  All contributions go directly to enrichment and learning activities, 
not to administrative costs.
</P>
<P>Contributions will be publicly recognized unless the donor wishes to remain 
anonymous.  Further questions may be answered by members of the citizen-based board 
of trustees or the Foundation Director, Sheryl Allen.
</P>
<P><B>Foundation, 451-1180</B></P>
<H1>
Parent Teacher Association (PTA)
</H1>
<P>PTA is a national volunteer organization dedicated to the welfare of all children.  A 
local unit operates in every elementary and secondary school in the Davis School District.  
The mission of the PTA is three-fold:
</P>
<P>1.  To support and speak in behalf of children and youth in the schools, in the 
community and before governmental agencies and other organizations that make 
decisions affecting children;
</P>
<P>2.  To assist parents in developing the skills they need to raise and protect their children; 
</P>
<P>3.  To encourage parent and public involvement in the public schools of this nation.
</P>
<P>PTA in Davis District works very hard to involve parents in programs and decisions 
that will directly affect their children.  Programs range from local programs such as 
health screenings, self-esteem building, classroom helpers, and parenting classes to input 
on District policy and lobbying on legislative issues regarding children.
</P>
<P>There is a place for every parent in PTA regardless of time or interests.  Becoming 
a member is easy.  Contact your local school for information, and then join in a 
combined effort that makes a difference for all the children in Davis District.</P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
<HR>&copy; 1996 Davis School District &copy;<BR>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:brad@cc.davis.k12.ut.us">brad@cc.davis.k12.ut.us</A></ADDRESS><!--(c) 1994 Davis School District-->
