<BODY BGCOLOR="#c6d3ad">
<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Spectrum (Gifted and Talented)

</H1>
<P>The District's Spectrum Program provides opportunities and options for gifted 
and talented students within the educational system and is driven by the individual needs 
of the student.
</P>
<H3>Basic Classroom Spectrum Program
</H3>
<P>The K-12 education program is based on the Spectrum Policy adopted in June, 1992.  
 This policy suggests that a &quot;Spectrum of opportunities, resources, and encouragement 
be provided to each student based on that student's needs and talents.&quot;  These needs 
and talents are met through the use of the Talents Unlimited Model for creative and 
critical thinking, Differentiated Curriculum, as well as Curriculum Compacting.  The 
Spectrum Program is working to provide this in each classroom in the Davis District.
</P>
<H3>Elementary Spectrum programs:
</H3>
<UL>
<LI>     Schoolwide Enrichment Model (SEM) is the neighborhood school program based 
on Renzulli's Triad.  SEM provides a wide variety of enrichment activities for the 
entire school, as well as for a smaller group of students called the Talent Pool.
</LI>
<LI>     Satellite is a full-time accelerated academic program for high achieving students 
in grades 3, 4, 5 and 6 at four magnet locations:  Cook, Morgan, Valley View 
and Washington elementaries.
</LI>
</UL>

<H3>Secondary Spectrum opportunities:
</H3>
<UL>
<LI>     Autonomous Learner Model (ALM) classes are offered in some grades 7-12 as an 
elective class for creatively gifted students.  The Betts Five Dimension Model guides 
students through an in-depth study of personal interest.
</LI>
<LI>     Honors and Accelerated classes are offered in some subject areas at the junior and 
senior high schools.  Students deal with issues, problems, and themes related to the 
subject using higher order thinking and talent skills.
</LI>
<LI>     Advanced Placement classes provide an option for seniors in high school who 
are college-bound students.
</LI>
</UL>


<H3>Spectrum opportunities, grades K-12:
</H3>
<UL>
<LI>     Talents Unlimited is the model for integrating critical and creative thinking with 
the Davis Course of Study.
</LI>
<LI>     Excel provides summer and before or after school enrichment classes at 
individual schools.
</LI>
</UL>

<P>
<B>Gifted and Talented, 451-1111</B></P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
