<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1>
<H2></H2>
<H2>Information Access
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>     If you have questions about which school your child will attend, call the Planning Office, <BR>
451-1356.
</LI>
<LI>     Patrons with questions or concerns about any school situation are encouraged to 
contact the teacher or staff member closest to the situation.  The next step is to 
communicate with the school principal.  If necessary, concerns may be brought to the attention of 
a District area director.  If the matter remains unresolved, it should be brought to 
the superintendent of schools.
</LI>
<LI>     Along with school newsletters, a District publication called 
<U>FOCUS</U> reports student testing, finances, statistics and other information regarding curriculum, 
instruction, growth and other District business.
</LI>
<LI>     If you have any questions regarding student placement, contact your school.</LI>
</UL>
<H2></H2>
<H2>Volunteer Opportunities
</H2>
<P>Thousands of volunteers have helped their schools and teachers with a variety of 
tasks and have provided additional help for one-on-one student instruction.  Volunteers 
donate countless hours through the PTA and play an important role in education.  Some 
volunteers have contributed as members of District and school committees in studying issues 
on community councils and as members of the District's Board of Education.
</P>
<P>Becoming a volunteer requires two elements - the desire to help children and 
some spare time.  If you wish to donate your time to a school or to a District program, please:
</P>
<UL>
<LI>     Contact the principal, the PTA president of the school or your child's teacher.
</LI>
<LI>     Contact District Volunteer Services, 451-1285.</LI>
<LI>Plan for a few hours of training after you have been placed.
</LI>
</UL>
<P><B>Volunteer Services, 451-1285</B></P>
