<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Plant Operations

</H1>
<P>Plant Operations consists of the Maintenance and Custodial Departments. 
Plant Operations is responsible for the maintenance and cleanliness of the following:</P>
<UL>
<LI>     70 schools and six support facilities
</LI>
<LI>     893 acres of landscaped grounds, playing fields and playgrounds
</LI>
<LI>     2,482,029 square feet in elementary schools
</LI>
<LI>     1,496,401 square feet in junior high schools
</LI>
<LI>     2,052,622 square feet in high schools
</LI>
<LI>     904,384 square feet in support facilities
</LI>
<LI>     228 portable/relocatable classrooms (included in square footage)
</LI>
</UL>
<P>Maintenance receives approximately 16,131 job sheets and 1,611 maintenance 
work requests each year for projects in schools.  Ninety-four full-time and 125 temporary 
summer employees cover many responsibilities:
</P>
<UL>
<LI>Cabinetry           </LI>
<LI>Locksmith
</LI>
<LI>Carpentry          </LI>
<LI>Masonry
</LI>
<LI>Electrical          </LI>
<LI>Motors and Refrigeration
</LI>
<LI>Electronics/Safety/Repairs          </LI>
<LI>Paint/Glass
</LI>
<LI>Equipment/Welding          </LI>
<LI>Plumbing
</LI>
<LI>Grounds/Repairs          </LI>
<LI>Roofing
</LI>
<LI>HVAC (heating, ventilation and air conditioning)          </LI>
<LI>Small Capital outlay</LI>
<LI>
</LI>
</UL>






<P>   
<U><B>The Custodial Department</B></U> , with three coordinators , has 127 full-time and 405 
part-time custodians.  Many of our part-time workers are high school or college students.  Each 
day the custodial staff cleans up after 58,000 students and sweeps or vacuums some 
6,031,052 square feet of floor space (including portable classrooms).  They trim, weed and 
manicure 893 acres of grounds.  The custodial department is not only involved with the daily 
cleaning of the building, but is also a service oriented group, setting up for various activities:
</P>
<UL>
<LI>     Set up and take down 960 cafeteria tables for the school lunch program each day. 
</LI>
<LI>     Pull out bleachers, set up gyms and/or multipurpose rooms for basketball, 
wrestling, city athletic activities and civic events.
</LI>
<LI>     Snow removal from miles of sidewalks and stairs.
</LI>
<LI>     Stock supplies in the teachers' work rooms.
</LI>
<LI>     Check off, receive and deliver  all supplies coming into the building.
</LI>
<LI>     Conduct daily safety checks of the boilers and mechanical equipment.
</LI>
<LI>     Conduct monthly fire extinguisher checks.
</LI>
<LI>     Conduct monthly safety checks of the building(s).
</LI>
<LI>     Stock heavy storage items for food service.
</LI>
</UL>
<P><B>Plant Operations, 774-7480 or 298-0238</B></P>
