<BODY BGCOLOR="#c6d3ad">
<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>Safe Schools

</H1>
<P>The Davis County School District updated the Safe School Policy and it was 
approved by the Board of Education on December 5, 1995.  The intent of the policy is to provide 
a safe learning and teaching environment for students and staff.  A due process 
procedure for students caught in violation of the policy is an integral part of the policy.
</P>
<P>The policy requires Drug Free and Weapon Free zones at all school sites, facilities 
and buses.  All school activities are to be considered Drug and Weapon Free zones 
regardless of the location.  The policy clearly identifies what the District considers a violation, 
provides administrators with an investigation process and suggests the disciplinary action to 
be pursued should an infraction occur.
</P>
<P>Each classroom and school has a discipline plan and schools work with 
their communities to develop, refine and communicate their plan.  Student, teacher 
and administrator responsibilities are clearly spelled out.
</P>
<P>If a student does make a poor decision in relation to the Safe School Policy, he or 
she will be given the opportunity to discuss it with the administrator.  The administrator 
may involve the local law enforcement if a trained investigator is required to resolve the 
situation or if a serious violation takes place. 
</P>
<P>A serious violation of law or school policy will result in suspension, expulsion 
or exclusion.  Suspension is usually 10 school days or less.  Expulsion is removal from 
the school for a period longer than 10 days.  Exclusion is the ending of:  educational 
services, participation in any school or district activities and prohibits entering on district or 
school premises for a fixed or indefinite period of time.
</P>
<P>A violation under the Safe School Policy does not need to result in a conviction in 
court for the District to discipline a student according to the policy.
</P>
<P><B>The Davis School District Board of Education is committed to a quality 
educational experience for students and staff.  A major component of this 
educational process is safety for all.</B></P>


<P><I><FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="AADCSTOC.HTM">Back</A></FONT></I></P>
<HR>&copy; 1996 Davis School District &copy;<BR>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="mailto:brad@cc.davis.k12.ut.us">brad@cc.davis.k12.ut.us</A></ADDRESS><!--(c) 1994 Davis School District-->
