<BODY BGCOLOR="#c6d3ad">
<H2><I>All about . . .</I></H2>
<H1><FONT COLOR="Green" SIZE="+5">D</FONT><FONT SIZE="+5">AVIS COUNTY SCHOOLS</FONT></H1><H1><FONT COLOR="Lime" SIZE="+5"></FONT>SAT Scores Consistent, Above State and Nation 

</H1>
<P>The SAT results for Davis county indicate all District averages are at or above 
State averages in grades 5, 8 and 11.  The Davis District grade level averages are also within 
the &quot;expected ranges&quot; as determined by the Utah State Office of Education in all subcategories. 
 Eighth grade math and reading scores were slightly lower than previous years and the 
fifth grade language score was four points higher.
</P>
<P>Because SAT scores are related to socioeconomic factors they are commonly 
reported within comparison bands.  The &quot;expected range&quot; is based on the scores of similar 
schools with comparable socioeconomic and demographic conditions, which allows for 
more informed and accurate comparisons.
</P>
<P>SAT Tests are taken in the fall at schools throughout the District and scores are 
median scores (middle scores).
</P>
<P><B>Testing, 546-7995</B>
</P>


<P><B>     </B><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="SAT.JPG"></P>
