<HTML>
<HEAD>
<LINK REV="made" HREF="WWW@CC.DAVIS.K12.UT.US">
<!-- OWNER_INFO="45 E State St Farmington UT 84025" -->

<TITLE>Community Education</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="O027.JPG">
<P ALIGN="center">
 
<IMG SRC="Mg1.gif"></P>

<CENTER>
<H2>
<FONT SIZE="7">Bountiful High</FONT><BR>
695 S. Orchard Drive</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>Registration: Jan. 6, 7, 8 from 6-8 PM at BHS. Please register at the Bountiful High School<BR>
Office at this time. Classes start week of Jan. 13. If the director is not available, please leave work and home phone numbers with the office secretaries and the director will return your call. Director: Cal Harris, Phone: 299-2055. </P>
<P>No Classes Are Held When Daytime School Is Not Held.<BR>
<B><BR>
</B><B>Aerobic Exercise 20/20 Program (Low Intensity)</B><BR>
Tarbet Dance St. T&amp;TH 1/14<BR>
10 Wks 5:30-6:30 PM $25<BR>
Introducing the new 20/20 program-a step class using benches with little or no impact for 20 minutes followed by 20 minutes of low impact aerobics and then power toning using bands. This is  an excellent class for both the beginner and experienced in aerobics, but modifications will be stressed for persons who need a lower intensity workout.</P>
<P><B>American Sign Language</B><BR>
Roberts Rm 807 T 1/14<BR>
6 Wks 7:00-8:30 PM $35</P>
<P>This course will provide an introduction to American Sign Language and discuss various<BR>
applications of signing in today&#146;s world. Participants will learn the finger spelled alphabet, signed number system, and various signed phrases that will help facilitate communication with the deaf. </P>
<P><B>Basket Weaving-Native American Twined Basketry Weaving</B><BR>
Dean Rm 226 T 1/21<BR>
1 Wk 7-9 PM $10</P>
<P>Dean Rm 226 T 2/11<BR>
1 Wk 7-9 PM $10</P>
<P>In this hands-on class for beginners, students will weave a small twined &#147;gift&#148; basket while learning the history and traditional uses of baskets from an anthropologist. This is an excellent class formteachers, scout leaders, or others who work with children and would like to pass on a new skill.<BR>
Note: Students should wear clothes that they don&#146;t mind getting wet. $10 materials fee per<BR>
person payable at class time. Ages nine-adult.</P>
<P><B>Ceramics</B><BR>
Arbon Rm 232 T 1/14<BR>
8 Wks 7-9 PM $45</P>
<P>Learn the techniques of making pottery on the potters wheel; or learn to make pottery by hand building. A small cost will be required for a ceramic tool set or for larger amounts of clay use.</P>
<P><B>Computer-Computer Aided Design</B><BR>
Price Rm 805 W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks 6:30-8:30 PM $45</P>
<P>A basic class in the use of CAD, AUTOCAD, VERSACAD, and CAD KEY. Design your own floor plans, business cards, inventions, or just have fun with the fascinating world of CAD. Enrollment for beginners through experienced with computers.</P>
<P><B>Computer-&#147;I Can&#146;t Believe What My Computer Can Do!</B>&#148; <BR>
Stapler Rm 804 T 1/14<BR>
8 Wks 7-9 PM $40 </P>
<P>This course is designed for those who are knowledgeable with the basics of WordPerfect for Windows 6.0/6.1 and who want to create real-world projects. Topics will include What is Desk Top Publishing?, Letterhead, Business Cards, Flyers, Post Cards, Booklets, Brochures, Newsletters, and WP Draw. Though the course will be taught using 6.0 the exercises will work with 6.1 as well. The instructor has won awards for her work in desk top publishing. Lab fee included in fee.</P>
<P><B>Computer-Introduction to the Internet and How to Use it</B><BR>
Thacker Rm 804 W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks 7-9 PM $40</P>
<P>This class is designed to introduce the basic concepts ofthe Information Highway (Internet).<BR>
Classes will give you the basic tools for exploring and retrieving information from the Internet (Telnet, FTP, Gopher, and e-mail will be discussed), The last two classes will be spent individualizing the use of Internet information to meet the needs of businesses, homeowners, students and professionals. It is not necessary to own a computer to benefit from this class. Lab fee included in fee.</P>
<P><B>Computer-Introduction to Word Perfect For Windows &amp; Intro to Computer Use</B></P>
<P>Stapler Rm 804 Th 1/16<BR>
8 Wks 7-9 PM $40</P>
<P>This class will teach word processing and computer use. It will teach the beginner as well as those  wanting to learn the program Word Perfect for Windows. This class is helpful for learning any word processing program. Includes a lab fee.</P>
<P><B>Computer-Spreadsheets-Lotus-1, 2, 3 Clone and Quattro Pro</B><BR>
Maughan Rm 802 W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks 7-9 PM $40</P>
<P>It&#146;s as easy as 1, 2, 3 to learn Lotus and Quattro Pro commands to create budgets, figure loans, plan expenses, or other home or business finances. The instructor, Alan Maughan is a CPA and auditor. Includes a lab fee.</P>
<P><B>Dance - Ballroom Dance Workshop</B><BR>
Anderson Rm 230 Th 2/6<BR>
1 Wk 6:30-8:30 PM $15/person</P>
<P>Learn to dance the night away! Basic fundamentals of Waltz and Swing will be taught. Couples &amp; singles are welcomed. Call Margene Anderson 298-8047.</P>
<P><B>Dance - Latin Dance Workshop</B><BR>
Anderson Rm 230 Th 3/6<BR>
1 Wk 6:30-8:30 PM $15/person<BR>
Learn the cha-cha and tango. Couples and singles are welcomed. Call Margene Anderson<BR>
298-8047.</P>
<P><B>Fast Pitch Softball</B><BR>
Boy&#146;s Field house Balcony W 1/15<BR>
5 Wks 7-9 PM $35<BR>
Bountiful High School is offering Fast pitch softball lessons. Bring your own catcher. To register for this class, contact Mr. or Mrs. Vaughn at 292-2168.</P>
<P><B>Hand Spinning</B><BR>
Lytle Rm 105 W 1/22<BR>
4 Wks 7-9 PM $30<BR>
Learn to spin beautiful yarn. This class will cover choosing a fleece, washing and carding the<BR>
wool, and spinning various fibers on a hooked stick, drop spindle, and spinning wheel. Fiber and equipment will be provided for class use.</P>
<P><B>Money Management-Financial Planning</B><BR>
Bennett Rm 102 W 1/15<BR>
3 Wks 7-9 PM $10<BR>
Workshop includes instruction on investments, taxes, estate planning, and risk management.<BR>
Individualized advice will be given. The instructor is a professional in his field.</P>
<P><B>Nails Beautiful</B><BR>
Nelson Rm 202 Wed 1/15<BR>
4 Wks 7-9 PM $16<BR>
Save time and money by learning to do your own nails, using the &#147;New Glaze System&#148;. (Not an acrylic or gel-no odor, yellowing, burning or primers). Learn how to strengthen, extend and maintain your nails, along with polishing tips, basic manicuring and safety precautions. Nail kit fee of $28.50 to be paid first night of class. If you have questions, call Danielle at 597-8011.</P>
<P><B>Nutrition and Diet Seminar--Food For A Healthy Heart</B><BR>
Calder Rm 300 Wed. 1/15<BR>
2 Wks 7-9 PM $15<BR>
Learn many simple helps to reducing fat, saturated fat, cholesterol and sodium in the foods you   eat. Then, with the help of a Registered Dietitian, visit a local supermarket to see first hand how to pick the best and leave the rest!</P>
<P><B>Play Group/Baby-Sitting Co-op</B><BR>
1 evening each at Bountiful High School and Davis High School. This informational meeting is for people who are new to Davis County or newly stay-at-home moms who are interested in joining a fun, friendly group to find playmates for your children, babysitters, and maybe a friend or twom for you. Held at Bountiful High School on Jan 14th, Rm. 105, 7-9 PM, No charge.</P>
<P><B>Tae-Kwan Do Karate</B><BR>
Cramer Dance Studio T/Th 1/14<BR>
8 Wks 7-8:30 PM $40<BR>
Instructor is USTF certified and is a 4th degree black belt. This class is for all ranks including beginners ages 8-adult. Fee for 2 individuals from one immediate family is $35 per person, fee form 3 from one family is $30 per person. Class will run continuously with payment due at beginning of each 8 week period.</P>
<P><B>Window Treatments</B><BR>
Pack Rm 204 T 1/14<BR>
4 Wks 7-8:30 PM $35<BR>
Don&#146;t miss this opportunity to learn to make beautiful window treatments for your home at a  fraction of the cost, and learn from a professional in the field. Classes will include instruction for balloon shades, princillas, assorted valances and Roman shades.</P>
<P><B>Little Braves Wrestling</B><BR>
Pluim Boy&#146;s Gym T 1/14<BR>
5 Wks 5:30-6:30 $30<BR>
The basic rules and techniques of wrestling will be taught. The class is for boys of elementary grade levels, K-6. There will be four weeks of instruction followed by a one night tournament on Feb. 12. Fee includes T-shirt and ribbons. Two or more children from the same immediate family, $25 each.</P>
