<CENTER>
<H1>
<B>Davis Applied Technology Center</B></H1>
<H1>
<B><FONT SIZE="3">550 East 300 South, Kaysville</FONT></B></H1></CENTER>
<P><B><I>DATC</I></B> is an accredited public applied technology education  institution featuring open entry/open exit enrollment with  hands-on, self-paced training designed to lead to employment.  Services include assessment, counseling, career guidance, and job placement.  Students receive Certificates of Completion or Proficiency Certification.</P>
<P><B><U>TUITION AND FEES</U></B></P>
<P>Tuition for adult students is very reasonable.   <B>Financial </B><B>aid is available</B> for eligible students.  High school students can enroll in day or evening programs, full or part-time.  <B>Tuition for high school students is waived </B><B>when referred by their high school ATE Coordinator.</B> Credit toward high school graduation can be earned concurrently.</P>
<P>The cost of Extended Day programs varies based on the number of hours ** enrolled.<B>  Students must enroll in </B><B>Extended Day programs for a minimum of six hours </B><B>per week.  Courses subject to cancellation for </B><B>inadequate enrollment.</B></P>
<P><B>Cost based on hours attending per week (paid monthly):</B><BR>
<B>6-10 hrs   11-15 hrs   16-21 hrs   21-25 hrs   26-30 hrs</B><BR>
<B>$16</B><B> </B>   <B> $17</B><B> </B><B>         $21             $22</B><B> </B><B>    $23</B></P>
<P>A <B>$30 registration fee</B> will be charged at the time of initial registration and a <B>$20.00 re-enrollment fee</B> will be assessed after enrollment has been terminated for any period of time.  A <B>$5 monthly material and equipment </B><B>usage fee</B> will be included in the monthly tuition.<BR>
Tuition is due on the first day of each month.  A $5 late fee will be charged for tuition received after the first day. Students who have not paid their tuition by the tenth will be withdrawn.<BR>
**A student enrolled in regular day school programs will have their tuition calculated based on the total number of hours enrolled in both day and night school.</P>
<P><B><U>COLLEGE CREDIT</U></B><BR>
Courses below that are indicated with an asterisk (*) are articulated with similar instructional programs at state colleges and universities.  <B>College credit can be granted </B><B>for successful course completion</B>.</P>
<P><B><U>SUPPORT PROGRAMS</U></B><BR>
Success in applied technology training requires competency in the areas of reading and math.  DATC offers support programs for those who do not meet the minimum requirements for their chosen program.  </P>
<P>The new <B>Regional Education and Employment Center </B><B>(One Stop Center) </B>includes Turning Point which is the regional center for single parents and displaced homemakers, Utah State Office of Rehabilitation and Office of Family Support.  Other support programs include adult education for high school completion, job search training, job placement and balancing work &amp; family training.  </P>
<CENTER>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><B><U>Day Program Information<BR>
</U></B><B>Technical Day Programs<BR>
</B>Registration is by appt. <B>Call 593-2580 </B>for information.
</P>
