<BODY BACKGROUND="O027.JPG">
<P ALIGN="center">
 
<IMG SRC="Mg1.gif"></P>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<B><FONT SIZE="7">D</FONT></B><FONT SIZE="7"><B>avis High</B></FONT><B></B></H1>
<H1><B><FONT SIZE="4">325 South Main, Kaysville</FONT></B>
</H1>
</CENTER>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">For information and pre-registration to any of the classes below you should contact the instructor directly.  If you are unable to reach them, then contact one of the directors, Mr. Kelly Oram or Mr. Mike Gardner at Davis High at 546-7940.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Low Impact Aerobics</B><BR>
Allen  546-1858 T&amp;Th 1/14<BR>
8 Wks  7:00 pm   $25<BR>
Toning and aerobic workout.  Easy on the joints.  Few dance steps to learn--lose extra pounds.  Get into shape the fun way!</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Slim-For-Life</B><BR>
Two classes - 6:00-7:00 pm or 7:00-8:00 pm.  Classes begin Tuesday, January 7th and run through March 11th.  For more information call the American Heart Association at 322-5601.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Boy Scout Merit Badge Courses</B><BR>
Courses will be offered during seven sessions held throughout the school year.  Most classes are either 4 or 5 weeks in length, with one class hour each week.  Classes are held on Tues. and Wed. afternoons at 4 and 5 pm at Davis High School.  Fees range from $11 to $14, depending on the class, and are due on registration night. Registration is held in room 252 from 5:30-6:45 pm on the following dates: Jan. 7, Feb 11, Mar. 18, Apr. 22.  Classes for each session start approximately one week after the registration.  Call Dave King at 544-9553 (Hm) or 546-7940 (Wk) for more info. and specific schedules.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Wood Shop</B><BR>
Sorenson 544-7117 Th 1/16<BR>
8 Wks  7 pm  $50<BR>
This class provides an opportunity for the beginning and experienced wood worker to manufacture a project of their own choice in an excellent facility.   Materials are available at reasonable prices.  Expert advice when needed.  Call instructor for further information and pre-registration.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Beginning Word Processing</B><BR>
Garrett  Rm.488  M 1/13<BR>
4 Wks  6:30-9:30 pm $30<BR>
This course is designed as an introduction to personal computers and word processing.  You will learn fundamental word processing skills such as creating, editing, spell checking and printing documents.  This class is limited to the first 20 participants.  Contact Kari Garrett at 547-0552 for pre-registration.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Advanced Word Processing</B><BR>
Garrett  Rm. 488  M 1/24<BR>
4 Wks  6:30-9:30 pm $30<BR>
If you have a basic understanding of personal computers and word processing, but would like to learn some of the additional capabilities of word processing.  Contact Kari Garrett at 547-0552 for pre-registration.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Family Photo Albums - How to Begin</B><BR>
Murray  544-5396 Th 1/23<BR>
1 wk  6:30-9:30 pm $8<BR>
Learn creative tips such as photo cropping, decoration, photo journaling, album page layout ideas and more. Learn information about the damaging effects of acid and PVC pages.  Class size limited.  <B>Materials fee of $5.</B>  Pre-register by calling Mary Murray at 544-5396.  This class will be repeated on Wednesday, Jan. 29, and Thursday, February 20th.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>The Ancient Art of Belly Dance</B><BR>
Harrow  773-1052 W 1/ 15<BR>
8 Wks  8:00-10:00 pm $35<BR>
Belly Dance is a wonderful form of self-expression  as well as a great way to firm and tone the body. Men and women over the age of 16 are welcome. Wear comfortable, work-out type clothing with ballet slippers or bare feet. We will learn belly dance steps and a choreography, Middle Eastern folk dances, how to play finger cymbals (zills). Call Courtney Harrow at 773-1052 to pre-register.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Beginning Fly Fishing</B><BR>
Navidomskis 497-9356 M    1/13 <BR>
6 Wks  7:15-9:45 pm  $35  20 hrs.<BR>
Navidomskis 497-9356 W    1/15 <BR>
6 Wks  7:15-9:45 pm  $35  20 hrs.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">The ideal class for anyone who would like to learn to fly fish.  <U>No experience necessary</U>.  However, novice and intermediate fishermen are welcome.  The class is quite comprehensive, covering all the basic information and techniques used in fly fishing.  The course will also include a five hour field trip to a local fly fishing location for some expert  instruction. </P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Pre-Registration is recommended</B><BR>
1.  General equip. &amp; tech. (dry fly, nymphing,                streamer)<BR>
2.  Casting tech.  (river fishing and float tube)<BR>
3.  Entomology (stream and lake)<BR>
4.  Stream strategies (nymphing: knots, leaders,            reading, drifts)<BR>
5.  Fly-tying (many variations &amp; techniques)<BR>
6.  Fly-tying (review of local patterns and fisheries) <BR>
<B>Lab fee $5.00 (Fly-tying materials)</B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Womens Weight Lifting</B><BR>
De Rouchey    581-9632 M &amp; W 1/13<BR>
8 Wks  6:30-7:30 pm $40<BR>
Women who would like to begin, maintain or develop a body conditioning program using weights as the primary tool.  The course will include the proper techniques used for warm-up, lifting, and cool down.   Call Jody De Rouchey at 581-9632 to pre-register.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Mens Weight Training</B><BR>
Jones  546-8061 M &amp; W 1/13<BR>
8 Wks  5:30-6:30 pm $40<BR>
This course is for men who wish to begin a weight training program using free weights.  Expert instruction will be provided in proper technique, tailored to fit your individual desires. Call Russ Jones at 546-8061 to pre-register.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Womens Volleyball</B><BR>
Ladies, a great way to keep in shape.  For more information call Glena Rigby at 451-2535 or Marie Mower at 544-4865.  Register the week of Dec. 30th through Jan. 3rd.  Play begins January 14th and 15th.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Cooking Kids</B><BR>
Balling  546-3984 Wed.  1/22  or Thurs. 1/23 4:00 pm          6 Wks.    $25.00<BR>
KIDS--IT'S YOUR TURN IN THE KITCHEN!  This is your chance to start your own recipe book, learn good cooking skills, and bring something home for the family.  Class meets once a week for six weeks.  Class size is small, so call Sandy now to reserve a space.  Ages fourth through sixth grade.  Register by calling Sandy Balling, 546-3984.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Play Group/Baby Sitting Co-op</B><BR>
People who are new to Davis County or newly stay-at-home moms who are interested in joining a fun, friendly group to find play mates for your children, babysitters and maybe a friend or two for you.  The meeting will be held on Wed., January 15th, at 7:00 PM in Port.  #2.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">
<B>You can earn your diploma now!!</B><BR>
If you are over 18 and would like to earn a high school diploma, review your current credit status towards graduation by contacting an Adult High School Coordinator at your local high school or call Sandra Tsushima at 546-7348 to schedule a credit evaluation meeting. One quarter credit is available for completing your evaluation, assessment and educational plan.<BR>
<B>Why Wait</B></P>
