<BODY BACKGROUND="O027.JPG">
<P ALIGN="center">
 
<IMG SRC="Mg1.gif"></P>

<CENTER>
<H1>
<B>L</B><B>ayton High</B><BR>
<B><FONT SIZE="3">440 Lancer Lane</FONT></B></H1>
</CENTER>
<P>For information on any class and pre-registration contact the director, Lincoln Hatch at Layton High <B>546-7950 </B>or <B>evenings 546-1978.</B>  Pre-registration will be January 6-10 and classes will begin the week of Jan 13.  You may also register during the first week of class.</P>
<P><B>Advanced WordPerfect</B><BR>
Norton  Rm 266  T&amp;TH 2/11<BR>
4 Wks    7:30-9:00  $35<BR>
Learn how to use WordPerfect's advanced features! This class can help you be more productive at work , in school, or help you make your communications more creative.  We will learn how to create tables and outlines, use mail merge, add graphics and use other WordPerfect advanced capabilities.</P>
<P><B>Auto Mechanics</B><BR>
Campbell Shop  T 1/14<BR>
8 Wks    6:00-9:00 pm $45<BR>
This is an open class where members work on their own autos. John Cline will be the instructor to help members on an individual basis.<B> </B></P>
<P><B>Computers Introduction to Windows</B><BR>
Bennett Rm 266  W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks    6:30-8:00 pm $35<BR>
This class is designed to teach windows and programs affiliated with windows and any general windows software,  also an introduction and use of the mouse.  </P>
<P><B>Golf Club Construction</B><BR>
Staff  Rm 147  W 1/15<BR>
3 Wks    6:00-8:00 pm  $25<BR>
This class is designed for those people who would like to make that special club or clubs, i.e., titanium driver with a graphite shaft. Learn how to regrip your own clubs, basically how you can save money and get the clubs you want and need.</P>
<P><B>Intermediate Gold Prospecting</B><BR>
Lindsay Rm S-12 Th 1/16<BR>
6 Wks    6:00-8:00 pm $35<BR>
The purpose of this class is to provide practical and useful information to the gold prospector, not only of how and where to find gold, but how tp produce, process and market it. The art of panning is thoroughly discussed and demonstrated along with dredging, sluicing, separating and cleaning. This class is primarily for the person who has had no previous experience or knowledge of prospecting or mining.</P>
<P><B>Introduction To and use of The Internet</B><BR>
Wilson  Library  Th 1/16<BR>
6 Wks  6:00-8:00 pm $40<BR>
This class is designed to introduce the basic concepts of the information highway (Internet).  Classes will give you the basic tools for exploring and retrieving information from the Internet (telnet, gopher, ftp, and e-mail will be discussed).</P>
<P><B>Introduction to Computers</B><BR>
Norton  Rm 166  T&amp;Th 1/14<BR>
4 Wks  6-7:30 pm  $35  <BR>
Have you been wanting to learn how to use your computer? This class is for you.  We will review the basic skills you need to know to use a PC (DOS based) computer.  We will cover the basics of DOS 5.0 while introducing the basic principles of word processing, spreadsheet, and desktop publishing software.</P>
<P><B>Introduction To Computers</B> <BR>
Norton  Rm 166  T&amp;Th 2/11<BR>
4 Wks  6-7:30 pm  $35 <BR>
Same as above.</P>
<P><B>Intro To WordPerfect 7.0 and 6.0</B><BR>
Norton  Rm 266           T&amp;Th 1/14<BR>
4 Wks  7:30-9:00  $35<BR>
If you have been wanting to learn how to use WordPerfect now is the time.  We will learn how to create, edit, print, and save documents including learning how to use thesaurus.  Register for the first class so you can continue learning in the advanced Word Perfect class.</P>
<P><B>Math, ACT and College Board Math </B><B>Preparation</B><BR>
Staff  Rm 147  W 1/15<BR>
6 Wks  6:30-8:00 pm  $30    <BR>
This course is intended to review skills through trigonometry to individually identify student differences and to help ready them. The course will offer sample ACT math tests and allow to solve problems individually, collectively and with teacher involvement. An excellent chance to ensure higher ACT math scores.  </P>
<P><B>Nails Beautiful</B><BR>
Canova Rm S14  T 1/23<BR>
4 Wks  7:00-9:00 pm $16<BR>
Save time and money by learning to do your own nails, using the &quot;new glaze system&quot; (not an acrylic or gel no primers, odors, or yellowing) During this four week course you will learn how to strengthen, extend, and safety precautions. <B>Nail kit fee of $28.50 </B><B>to be paid first night of class</B>. For more information call Debbie 774-5988.  Registration limited  register early.</P>
<P><B>Painting</B><BR>
Marx  Rm 159  W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks  6:30-8:30 pm  $40<BR>
Explore the basics of painting.  Bring your choice of watercolors, oils or acrylics.  We will discuss painting techniques and art concepts. We will adapt the lessons to fit your own personal needs.</P>
<P><B>Photography</B><BR>
Curtis  Rm 165  W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks    7:00-9:00 pm $40<BR>
Experience the thrill of developing and printing your own black and white photographs.  Learn about different types of cameras and the advantage of each.  Also learn how to use a manual SLR camera. Learn how to compose more interesting photographs by applying art concepts like value, space, proportions, etc.  You will need to have access to a 35mm or 120 camera, other supplies may be purchased from the instructor.  Limited to 10 students, sign up early.</P>
<P><B>Spanish I</B><BR>
Ferrin   Rm 143  T&amp;Th 1/14<BR>
9 Wks     7:00-8:00  $40 <BR>
No previous experience is required.   Introduction into basic conversational and practical skills in Spanish with focus on listening, speaking, reading, and writing.  Present tense, command forms, and false future tense of selected regular and irregular verbs will be presented and practiced. Quick start communication skills will also be emphasized for professionals and tourists.  (high school students may also take this class to make up one term of high school Spanish I with two tests and 8 written assignments not require of adult participants.)</P>
<P><B>Spanish II</B><BR>
Ferrin   Rm 143  T&amp;Th 1/14<BR>
9 Wks    8:00-9:00 pm  $40<BR>
Spanish I class highly recommended.  Additional practice in basic skills in listening, speaking, reading, and writing. Preterite, imperfect, future, and present subjunctive verb tenses will be presented in contextwith emphasis on improving communication skills for professionals and or potential travelers. ( High school student may take this class for credit to make one term of high school Spanish II.)</P>
<P><B>Western Dance Class</B><BR>
Bushaw Commons Th 1/16<BR>
6 Wks  7:00-9:00 pm $30 person<BR>
Learn the latest line dances, partner line dances, and Western Swing.</P>
<P><B>Wood Working</B><BR>
Aldridge Rm S14  W 1/15<BR>
9 Wks  6:00-9:00 pm $50<BR>
Individual instruction to design, make, and finish own projects, with safe usage of hand and power equipment.  Bring your own material to start on projects.</P>
<P><B>Word Processing for Windows</B><BR>
Bennett Rm 266  W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks     8:00-9:30 pm $35<BR>
Learn the basics of this powerful word processing and desktop publishing program.  Let the program do most of your work for you. Learn how to format letters, tables, flyers, signs, newsletters, graphics, and much more.</P>
<CENTER>
<P ALIGN="CENTER"><B>Family Enrichment Classes</B></P></CENTER>
<P><B>Parent Workshops</B><BR>
These classes are for parents with children from birth to five.  We will meet every Tuesday at 7:00 pm at the Family Enrichment Center at 320 S 500 E Kaysville. Lessons will be short with lots of question and answer time.  We will address needs of children with disabilities too.  <B>There is no charge for these classes!</B> If you have any questions regarding the workshops, please call Anita Davenport at 546-7309 ext. 120.</P>
<P>Jan.  7 <U>Family Fun</U> - Interactive games to help build family unity.  We will play games.<BR>
Jan. 14 <U>Power Of Choice</U> - 4 week class - Part I:  Growing up and making choices, choosing  a vision.<BR>
Jan. 21 <U>Power Of Choice</U> - Part II: Initiative, act  don&#146;t react, see the consequences.<BR>
Jan. 28 <U>Power Of Choice</U> - Part III: Perspective,  seeing the big picture.<BR>
Feb. 4 <U>Power Of Choice</U> - Part IV: Building self- esteem in children.<BR>
Feb. 11 <U>Ask A Nurse Night</U><BR>
Feb. 18 <U>Don</U><U>&#146;t Pop Your Cork</U> - Stress Reduction <BR>
Feb. 25 <U>Left Brain-Right Brain Learning</U> -   Understanding how the brain takes in  information and uses it.<BR>
Mar. 4 <U>Learning Styles</U> - Helping your child to be a  winner.  How to unlock your child&#146;s  creativity.<BR>
Mar. 11 <U>Where Do We Go From Here</U> - Discussion  of &#147;Transition of Children with individual  education plans into kindergarten.<BR>
Mar. 18 <U>Raising A Thinking Child</U> - I can problem  solve revisited.  Helping your child get  along with others.<BR>
Mar. 25 No Class This Week<BR>
Apr. 1 <U>Songs and Finger Plays for Coordination</U><BR>
Apr. 8 <U>Color Me Red, Blue, White or Yellow</U> -  Personality Inventory<BR>
Apr. 15 <U>How to Help Your Child Deal With Crisis</U><BR>
Apr. 22 <U>Alternatives to Television</U><BR>
