<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Astrology - Beginning<BR>
</B>Richman Rm 265  T 1/23<BR>
5 Wks  6-8 pm  $50</P>
<CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER>

<CENTER>
<CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER>
<CENTER><CENTER><CENTER><CENTER>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">This class provides an introduction to the skills necessary to create and understand a basic horoscope (map of the sky).  Specific topics include astrological symbols and their keywords.  How to use an Ephemeris.  The Zodia signs, planets houses and their basic attributes. References available upon request.  </P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>There is a $5 lab fee.</B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Astrology - Intermediate</B><BR>
Richman Rm 265  Th 1/23<BR>
5 Wks  6-8 pm  $50</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">This class provides a look at Natal, Transiting, Progressed, Synastry (Relationships) and Horary Charts.  Specific topics include the Chart Signature, Ascendant, Midheaven, Chart Rulers, Fixed Star Degrees, The Scout Planet, Major and Minor aspects, Prenatal Eclipses and the cycles of the Progressed Moon.  References available. </P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>$5 Lab Fee.</B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Auto Mechanics</B><BR>
Crowley Rm 120        T or Wed    1/7<BR>
10 Wks  7-10 pm  $55</P><P ALIGN="LEFT">Clay Crowley has been a student in auto shop for a number of years, and because of his expertise brings with him a lot of know-how about the maintenance of automobiles.  This course consists of minor repair and service to cars and pick-up trucks.  The instructor shows you how, and you do the repairs.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Computer - I</B><B>&#146;m on the Internet but I </B><B>want a WEB Page too!</B><BR>
Robles  Rm 115  Wed 1/22<BR>
7 Wks  8-10 pm $30</P><P ALIGN="LEFT">In just a few weeks you can put your own web page on the NET for all to see.   By the end of this course, you will have created your own web page. You will finish the course with the skills to create a web page and know how to update it <U>by yourself</U>.  Absolutely no prior knowledge required.  To reserve a seat prior to pre-registration, call774-6422.  Pre-registration will be held Monday, 1/13, in Room 115 from 6:00 to 7:30 pm. A $10 tech fee is required.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Computer Keyboarding</B><BR>
P.Wenzel Rm 120  Wed 1/22 <BR>
7 Wks  6-8 pm  $35</P><P ALIGN="LEFT">The computer keyboard is the most important device that is used to communicate with a computer.  The keyboard is necessary whether you are using computer for word-processing, spread sheeting, writing programs or manipulating files using the operating system.  The computer keyboard has three different functions: using the standard typewriter keys, using the number pad, using the programmable keys.  A $10 lab fee is required. To register call 295-8788. </P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>Pre-registration is recommended</U></B></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Computer - The Internet: What is it and </B><B>How do I get it</B><B>?</B></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT">Robles  Rm 115  Th  1/23<BR>
7 Wks  8-10 pm $10</P><P ALIGN="LEFT">What is all the fuss about?  What do I need to do to have it in the home?  Is it expensive?  No!  How does it compare to Compu Serv, Prodigy and America On-Line?  Take the next four weeks and open your world to the possibilities. A $10 tech fee is required.  To reserve a seat prior to pre-registration please call 774-6422. Pre-registration will be held Monday, 1/13, in Room 115 from 6:00 - 7:30 pm.</P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Computer - Word Processing </B><B>(WordPerfect Versions 6.0,6.1,or 7.0)</B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">Robles  Rm 115  Th 1/23<BR>
7 Wks  6 - 8 pm $30</P><P ALIGN="LEFT">From starting the program to saving files, this course will highlight WordPerfect and Word for Windows. Understand Windows&#146; word processing and editing features for home, work, or hobby. Learn how to type, edit, copy, move, bold, underline, and size text in a letter to include placing in graphics.  This course will support students with no knowledge to intermediate users.  </P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>A $10 </B><B>tech fee is required</B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT">.  To reserve a seat prior to pre-registration call 774-6422.  Pre-registration will be held Monday, 1/13, in Room 115 from 6:00 - 7:30 pm.</P>
