<P ALIGN="LEFT">Robles  Rm 115  Wed 1/23<BR>
5 Wks  6-8 pm  $30</P><P ALIGN="LEFT">Learn what floppy disks are and how to read and save files, use software programs including the basics of Windows, the keyboard, and the mouse. Absolutely no prior knowledge required.  To reserve a seat prior to pre-registration, call 774-6422.  Pre-registration will be held Monday, 1/13, in Room 115 from 6-7:30 pm.  $10 tech fee required.</P><P ALIGN="LEFT"><B>Computer - Intro to Word for Windows</B><BR>
Patty Wenzel Rm 120  Wed 1/23<BR>
7 Wks  8-10 pm $35</P><P ALIGN="LEFT">This course is designed for those who want to learn Microsoft&#146;s Word 6.0 for Windows using Windows 3.1 or 3.11. . You will learn how to use the many differenct fonts that are available.  You will learn how to cut, copy and past using the editor.   You will learn how to interact between Word and Excel or any of the many other Window's products.   A $10 lab fee for the manual is required.  Pre-registration is recommended.  Please call 295-8788.</P>
