<P><B>Firearms Safety and Concealed</B><B> Firearms License</B>   <BR>
Madsen  Room 214 Th 1/30<BR>
4 Wks  7-9 p.m.  $40<BR>
There are two reasons why you would want to take this class: If you have a limited knowledge about firearms safety and would like to learn more, or if you have a need to, or just want to apply for a Concealed Firearms Permit, then this class is for you. The student who wants to apply for the Concealed Firearms permit will also need to fire a handgun at the firing range.</P>
<P><B>Hunter Safety Course</B><BR>
Madsen  Room 214 M&amp;W 9/13<BR>
4 Wks  7-9 p.m.  $10<BR>
The course teaches the student about firearms safety, hunting ethics, survival when lost and other skills to make hunting safe. One Saturday morning at the firing range -date and time to be announced. This course when completed to the required standards qualifies the individual student to receive a &quot;Blue Card&quot; proof of the completion of a hunter education course.</P>
<P><B>Financial Education/Successful</B> <B>Retirement Planning</B><BR>
Williams Room 306 W 2/4 <BR>
4 Wks  6:30-9 p.m. $49/Ind or couple<BR>
This seminar will show you a conservative approach to money management, estate planning, and wills and trusts. <U>The information you receive will pay dividends for the </U><U>rest of your life!</U> Your instructors provide information that is current, comprehensive and non-commercial. Materials provided.</P>
<P><B>Floral Design</B><BR>
Christensen (Ogden)    Room 110 W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks  7-9 p.m.  $40<BR>
Create beautiful floral arrangements from fresh flowers, dried and silk flowers, highlighting basic design concepts. Bring own scissors and sharp wire cutters to the first class. There will be an additional fee for materials used. The class will have a 12 student minimum and be limited to a maximum of 19 students.</P>
<P><B>German - Beginning</B><BR>
Teeples  Room 211 T 1/21<BR>
6 Wks  6-7:30 p.m. $35<BR>
This class is open to anyone who wishes to study German. No previous language study is necessary. An introduction to basic German vocabulary, grammar, songs, and culture in speaking, reading and writing.</P>
<P><B>German - Level 2</B><BR>
Teeples  Room 211 T 1/21<BR>
6 Wks  7-9:30 pm $35<BR>
This class is a continuation of the beginning German class, or for those who have learned a beginning German.</P>
<P><B>Russian - Beginning</B><BR>
Feinstein Room 202 T 2/11<BR>
6 Wks  6:30-8 p.m. $35<BR>
The class will be taught by Dmitry Feinstein, a recent Russian immigrant. He has a rich background in teaching music, English, Russian History and Russian as a language. </P>
<P><B>Spanish - Beginning</B><BR>
Anderson Room 210 W 1/15<BR>
6 Wks  6-7:30 p.m. $35<BR>
Introduction to basic Spanish vocabulary, grammar and culture.</P>
<P><B>Spanish - Level 2</B><BR>
Anderson Room 210 W 1/15<BR>
6 Wks  7:30-9 p.m. $35<BR>
This class is a continuation of the beginning Spanish class, or for those who have learned a beginning Spanish.</P>
<P><B>Investments for Beginners</B><BR>
Stephenson Room 211 W 1/15<BR>
8 Wks   7-8:30 p.m. $35 Ind./$50 Cpl..<BR>
Focus of the class will be on the fundamental aspects of investing in stocks, bonds, and annuities with particular emphasis on mutual funds and how they relate to planning for your financial future.</P>
<P><B>Jazz Dance</B><BR>
Morrell       Studio M&amp;W Continuous<BR>
Call for class time and prices.<BR>
Whether your goal is to dance professionally, musicals, drill teams, cheerleading, dance teams, or what to learn new moves or develop a talent and coordination, this dance program is for you. <B>A special class is offered for </B><B>Adults.</B>  For information, call Wendy 771-5720.</P>
<P><B>Basic Finishing School and Beginning</B> <B>Modeling</B><BR>
Badham  Room 211 Th 1/16<BR>
8 Wks  7-9 p.m . $40<BR>
Learn grooming techniques, makeup skills, diet, nutrition and exercise. Fashion flair - accessorizing and coordinating, modeling for a photographer, fashion show posing and routines, Voice Projection, and introduction to television. Receive an 8 X 10 photo of yourself. $10 of the tuition is for the photographer fee.</P>
<P><B>Photography 1</B><BR>
Boswell  Room 211 M 1/13<BR>
4 Wks  7-9:30 p.m. $30<BR>
Boswell  Room 211 M 2/17<BR>
4 Wks  7-9:30 p.m. $30<BR>
This 4 week class covers the &quot;Fundamentals of Photography&quot; and has been designed for both the beginner and the advanced amateur.  Learn about the camera, film, lights, filters, flash and more.  A camera is helpful but not necessary for the class. There is a minimum of 8-10 students required.</P>
<P><B>Seminars for Singles</B><BR>
Clegg  Room 305 Tues 1/14<BR>
5 Wks  7-9 p.m.  $25<BR>
Learn 21 new effective communication skills such as negotiating conflicts, meeting new people, creating breakthroughs, and getting past the <U>right</U> appearance. Come to as many sessions as you desire at just $5 per session or $20 for all  5 sessions, if paid on the first night. For more information, call Jay Clegg at 546-0650.</P>
<P><B>Parents Communicating with Teenagers</B><BR>
Clegg  Room 305 Th 1/16<BR>
3 Wks 7-9 p.m. $10 for 3 weeks/$5 for single classes<BR>
Parents can learn to recognize problems and learn how to expand their ability to  use communication skills in helping their teenagers. For more information, call Jay Clegg, 546-0650.</P>
<P><B>Square Dancing</B><BR>
Bronson Cafeteria  T January<BR>
Continuous 7-10 p.m. <BR>
Exciting club for couples of all ages. Lots of room for more &quot;new&quot; friends. New classes for this group start in October each year. For information, call Dot or Ray at 295-5839.</P>
<P><B>Weight Lifting - Co-ed Class</B><BR>
Magalei  New weight room    T &amp; Th   1/21<BR>
7 Wks  7-8:30 p.m.      $40<BR>
Beginner or advanced weight training, it doesn't matter. Everyone is invited. Come and try out our new weight room at WXHS. Bring a weight belt. 40 person maximum.</P>
<P><B>Wood Working</B><BR>
Paxman  Wood Shop T 1/28<BR>
8 Wks  6:30-9 p.m. $45<BR>
Complete woodworking facilities. Individualized instruction to fit your project.</P>
