<P ALIGN="center"><FONT SIZE="6">Effective Instructional Practices</FONT></P>

<HR>


<H3>ITI (SUSAN KOVALIK) STUDY GROUP </H3>
<P> <BR>
Jan. 7, Feb. 4, Mar. 4, Apr 8 &amp; May 6 <BR>
	COURSE #: 9602352<BR>
	PLACE: Hill Field Elementary<BR>
Jan 28, Feb 25, Mar 25, Apr 22 &amp; May 27<BR>
	COURSE #: 9602351<BR>
	PLACE: Woods Cross Elementary<BR>
(Same class taught twice)<BR>
Learn to create a brain compatible classroom using Susan Kovalik's ITI model.  Absence of threat, multiple intelligences, cooperative learning are used to enhance student learning.  Open to all teachers who have taken 3 day intensive as well as newcomers to this model. <BR>
	FOR: K-6 teachers<BR>
	INSTRUCTOR: Colleen Uhl &amp; Kristy 			      Zizumbo<BR>
	CREDIT: 1 credit hour<BR>
	COST:  $10<BR>
	TIME: 4:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m.<BR>
	LIMIT: 10 Minimum, 30 Maximum</P>
<H3><BR>
BASIC  COOPERATIVE LEARNING </H3>
<P><BR>
Jan. 9 16, 23, 30, Feb. 6, 13, 20 &amp; 27<BR>
Basic cooperative learning class using Spencer Kagan's Structures model.  Hands-on, easy to implement tools to create a collaborative atmosphere.<BR>
 	COURSE #: 9602339<BR>
	FOR: Teachers K-12<BR>
	INSTRUCTOR: Colleen Uhl &amp; 			      Winnie Lippold 	CREDIT: 2 credit hours<BR>
	COST:  $10<BR>
	PLACE: Bountiful  Elementary, Rm 31<BR>
	TIME: 4:00 to 6:30 p.m.<BR>
	LIMIT: 10 Minimum, 30 Maximum</P>
<P>&nbsp;	</P>
<H3>CO-OP ACROSS THE CURRICULUM</H3>
<P><BR>
Feb. 22, Mar. 22, Apr. 26 &amp; May 3<BR>
Follow-up class for those having taken Tribes or Basic Co-op.  Emphasis is on applying Cooperative Learning to content areas.<BR>
	COURSE #: 9602340<BR>
	FOR: 1-6 teachers<BR>
