<P ALIGN="center"><FONT SIZE="6">Invest in </FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="7">Futures</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="center"><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="FUTONE.GIF"></P>
<P><FONT SIZE="5"><B>Fact </B></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI>Teachers spend approximately $200 - over $1000 of personal funds annually to purchase basic classroom supplies.</LI>
</UL>
<P><B><FONT SIZE="5">Action</FONT></B><FONT SIZE="5"></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI>Your help is needed to <U><B>ADOPT-A-CLASS</B></U>. Provide monetary assistance or in-kind donations to one class during the school year. You determine your company's or family's ability to meet classroom and student needs.</LI>
</UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="5"><B>Result</B></FONT></P>
<UL>
<LI>Education, business, and families need one another. Education cannot effectively prepare students without vision provided by involved individuals. By getting involved, you will have a direct impact on the future.</LI>
</UL>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="-1">&quot;Three or four different magazine subscriptions would open up a whole new world of people, places, ideas, and cultures. It is a small request, but one that would make a real difference in the quality of teaching that I could provide.&quot; </FONT></I><BR>
<B>- Kathy Richardson, 3rd Grade Teacher<BR>
 Sara Jane Adams Elementary</B></P>
<P><B></B></P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="-1">Needs vary from class to class, but may include calculators, books, musical instruments, lab equipment, supplies, cash donations, etc.</FONT></I></P>
<P><I><FONT SIZE="-1"></FONT></I></P>
<P><FONT SIZE="+1">Please contact your school about ADOPT-A-CLASS opportunities.</FONT></P>
